text: 46 XX gonadal dysgenesis is a type of gonadal dysgenesis, which is characterized by the lack of functional ovaries to induce puberty in an otherwise 46,XX female. It is also known exactly as ovarian dysgenesis.
Hyperkalemic periodic paralysis is a type of familial periodic paralysis and is exactly synonymous with familial hyperkalemic periodic paralysis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypokalemic_periodic_paralysis rdfs:subClassOf :familial_periodic_paralysis ;
    :has_exact_synonym "Hypokalemic familial periodic paralysis"@en,
        "Periodic paralysis I"@en,
        "Westphal disease"@en,
        "familial hypokalemic periodic paralysis"@en,
        "familial periodic paralysis"@en,
        "periodic hypokalemic paralysis"@en .
text: Hypokalemic periodic paralysis is a type of familial periodic paralysis and has several exact synonyms. These synonyms include Hypokalemic Familial Periodic Paralysis, Periodic Paralysis I, Westphal Disease, Familial Hypokalemic Periodic Paralysis, Familial Periodic Paralysis, and Periodic Hypokalemic Paralysis.

Farmer's lung is a type of extrinsic allergic alveolitis, which is also known as Farmer's lung or farmer lung. It is characterized by being transmitted at least in part through airborne transmission and has symptoms including cough. Farmer's lung is defined as an extrinsic allergic alveolitis induced by the inhalation of spores (Aspergillus sp and thermophilic actinomycetes) in dust from moldy hay or straw, featuring a sudden onset, fever, cough, expectoration, and breathlessness.

Brucella melitensis brucellosis is a type of brucellosis that involves an infection caused by Brucella melitensis in cattle, goats, sheep, and humans. It is defined by having a material basis in some Brucella melitensis and is characterized by symptoms such as backache, anorexia, fever, and malaise. Additionally, the disease has symptoms including limb pain and back pain.

Brucella abortus brucellosis is a type of brucellosis, which has its material basis at least in part in Brucella abortus. This condition is characterized by a variety of symptoms including joint pain, weight loss, headache, fever, chills, and malaise. Specifically, Brucella abortus brucellosis is defined as a brucellosis that results from an infection caused by Brucella abortus in cattle and humans, manifesting symptoms such as fever, chills, sweats, weight loss, malaise, headaches, myalgia (muscle pain), and arthralgia (joint pain).

Hemangioma of the orbit is a type of orbital disease that at least derives from some endothelial cell, and it is located in the orbital region. Moreover, Hemangioma of the orbit has the exact synonym "Angioma of the orbit."
Cavernous hemangioma of the orbit is a type of cavernous hemangioma, and it is exactly synonymous with Cavernous Angioma of the orbit.

Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome is a type of nervous system disease that is defined as a nervous system disease characterized by hyperthermia, muscular rigidity, autonomic dysfunction, and altered consciousness. It is associated with the administration of antipsychotic and other central dopaminergic blockers.

Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome is a lung disease that falls under the category of viral infectious diseases. It is linked to a variety of symptoms including shock, headache, fever, cough, vomiting, pulmonary edema, muscle pain, and chills. The syndrome is characterized by its association with pulmonary infiltrates. It can be transmitted by various rodents including Oligoryzomys longicaudatus, Oryzomys palustris, Sigmodon hispidus, Myodes glareolus, and Calomys laucha. The disease is caused by several strains of Orthohantavirus, including Orthohantavirus andesense, Orthohantavirus bayoui, Orthohantavirus negraense, Orthohantavirus nigrorivense, and Orthohantavirus sinnombreense. Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome is defined as a viral infectious disease that results in infection located in the lung. It is transmitted by deer mouse (Myodes glareolus), cotton rat (Sigmodon hispidus), marsh rice rat (Oryzomys palustris), small vesper mouse (Calomys laucha), or rice rat (Oligoryzomys longicaudatus). The infection manifests symptoms such as fever, muscle pain, headache, cough, vomiting, and chills, which rapidly progress to bilateral interstitial pulmonary infiltrates, pulmonary edema, and hypoxia, often resulting in death from shock or cardiac complications.

Pemphigoid gestationis is a type of pemphigoid that intersects with conditions that, at minimum, exhibit the phenotype of abnormal immunoglobulin levels and are diseases located in areas comprising both skin and connective tissue. It is defined as a pemphigoid characterized by erythematous papules, vesicles, and plaques around the trunk and extremities that develop during pregnancy, particularly during the second and third trimesters. Pemphigoid gestationis has symptoms including pruritis and has a material basis in autoantibodies to the basement membrane, which triggers a complement cascade and attracts eosinophils to the subepidermis. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with both Gestational herpes and herpes gestationis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chorea_gravidarum rdfs:subClassOf :choreatic_disease .
text: chorea gravidarum is a type of choreatic disease.

Sporotrichosis is a type of primary systemic mycosis and also a type of condition that at least has a material basis in Sporothrix schenckii. It is defined as a primary systemic mycosis that results in a systemic fungal infection. This infection, which occurs in animals and humans, has its material basis in Sporothrix schenckii and results in the formation of a red papule at the site of inoculation.
Ureteral lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of ureter cancer, which is characterized by having a material basis in lymphocytes. It is also exactly synonymous with lymphoma of the ureter.
Regional ureteric cancer is a type of ureter carcinoma and is exactly synonymous with regional ureteric carcinoma as well as regional malignant ureteral tumor.
Dumping syndrome, a type of postgastrectomy syndrome, is also exactly synonymous with Dumping (jejunal) syndrome and Jejunal syndrome.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:wolman_disease rdfs:subClassOf :lysosomal_acid_lipase_deficiency ;
    :has_broader_match "ICD10CM:E75.5" ;
    :has_definition "A lysosomal acid lipase deficiency characterized by infantile onset of rapidly progressive accumulation of cholesteryl esters and triglycerides throughout the body, resulting in hepatosplenomegaly, severe malnutrition, jaundice, vomiting, diarrhea, steatorrhea. Death usually occurs within the first year of life." ;
    :has_exact_match "OMIM:620151",
        "ORDO:75233" ;
    :has_exact_synonym "acute infantile lysosomal acid lipase deficiency",
        "complete LAL deficiency",
        "complete LIPA deficiency",
        "complete cholesterol ester hydrolase deficiency",
        "complete lysosomal acid lipase deficiency",
        "Acid esterase deficiency"@en,
        "Acid lipase deficiency"@en,
        "Wolman xanthomatosis"@en,
        "Wolman's disease"@en,
        "Wolman's or triglyceride storage type III disease"@en,
        "Xanthomatosis, familial"@en .
text: Wolman disease is a type of lysosomal acid lipase deficiency characterized by infantile onset of rapidly progressive accumulation of cholesteryl esters and triglycerides throughout the body. This condition results in hepatosplenomegaly, severe malnutrition, jaundice, vomiting, diarrhea, steatorrhea, and usually leads to death within the first year of life. Wolman disease is also known by several exact synonyms including Acid esterase deficiency, Acid lipase deficiency, Wolman xanthomatosis, Wolman's disease, Wolman's or triglyceride storage type III disease, Xanthomatosis, familial, acute infantile lysosomal acid lipase deficiency, complete LAL deficiency, complete LIPA deficiency, complete cholesterol ester hydrolase deficiency, and complete lysosomal acid lipase deficiency. Furthermore, Wolman disease has a broader match with the ICD10CM code E75.5, and it has exact matches in medical databases such as OMIM:620151 and ORDO:75233.
Lipoid proteinosis is a type of lipid metabolism disorder, which is also exactly known as Lipid proteinosis and URBACH-WIETHE DISEASE.

Fabry disease is a type of sphingolipidosis characterized by the buildup of globotriaosylceramide in the body's cells, which is primarily due to X-linked inherited mutations in the GLA gene that encodes alpha-galactosidase A, located on chromosome Xq22. It is also known by several exact synonyms including Alpha-galactosidase A deficiency, Angiokeratoma Corporis Diffusum, Fabry Disease, Cardiac Variant, Fabry's disease, alpha galactosidase deficiency, and deficiency of melibiase.
Fucosidosis is a type of lysosomal storage disease, which is precisely synonymous with both A-fucosidase deficiency and alpha-fucosidase deficiency.

Sjogren Larsson Syndrome is a type of syndrome, specifically an autosomal recessive disease, that at least has a material basis in some form of autosomal recessive inheritance. It is characterized by ichthyosis, mental retardation, spastic paraparesis, macular dystrophy, and leukoencephalopathy. The syndrome has its material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutations in the aldehyde dehydrogenase 3 family member A2 (ALDH3A2) gene, which encodes fatty aldehyde dehydrogenase, on chromosome 17p11. Sjogren Larsson Syndrome is also known by several exact synonyms including FALDH deficiency, SLS, Sjogren Larsson syndrome, Sjogren-Larsson's syndrome, and fatty acid alcohol oxidoreductase deficiency.

Cholesterol ester storage disease is a type of lysosomal acid lipase deficiency characterized by onset in childhood or later of progressive accumulation of cholesteryl esters and triglycerides primarily in the liver and spleen. It is also known by its exact synonyms CESD, partial LAL deficiency, partial LIPA deficiency, partial cholesterol ester hydrolase deficiency, and partial lysosomal acid lipase deficiency. Furthermore, cholesterol ester storage disease is precisely matched with several databases, including GARD:12099, MESH:D015217, OMIM:278000, and ORDO:75234.
Neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis is a type of lipid storage disease and it is exactly synonymous with hereditary ceroid lipofuscinosis.

Niemann Pick disease is a type of sphingolipidosis and is characterized by the accumulation of the lipid sphingomyelin in lysosomes in cells. It has exact synonyms including Sphingomyelinase Deficiency Disease, lipoid histiocytosis, and sphingomyelin lipidosis.
Peripheral degeneration of the cornea is a type of corneal degeneration, and it is also exactly synonymous with peripheral degenerations of the cornea.

Candidal paronychia is a type of candidiasis and also a type of nail disease, specifically affecting the area around the nail where the disease manifests in the outer-most layer of the nail. It is caused by a fungal infection resulting from Candida species. This condition leads to a painful, red, swollen area around the nail, often at the cuticle or at the site of a hangnail or other injury. Additionally, candidal paronychia is precisely referred to as candidiasis of skin and nails, underlining its impact on these areas.

WAGR syndrome is a type of chromosomal deletion syndrome that is defined as a nephroblastoma, leading to a rare genetic syndrome in which affected children are predisposed to develop Wilms tumor, Aniridia (absence of the colored part of the eye, the iris), genitourinary anomalies, and mental retardation. This condition results from a deletion on chromosome 11, resulting in the loss of several genes, making it one of the best-studied examples of a condition caused by the loss of neighboring (contiguous) genes. WAGR syndrome is also known by its exact synonyms: 11p partial monosomy syndrome, Wilms tumor-Aniridia-Genitourinary Anomalies-Mental Retardation syndrome, and chromosome 11p13 deletion syndrome.
Partial arterial retinal occlusion is a type of retinal artery occlusion and it has exact synonyms, which include Retinal partial arterial occlusion and partial retinal arterial occlusion.

Argyll Robertson pupil is a type of abnormal pupillary function characterized by a small pupil, the absence of a pupillary light reflex, and the retention of a normal pupillary near response. It is also known by exact synonyms including Argyll Robertson phenomenon or pupil, nonsyphilitic, Argyll Robertson pupil, atypical, and Atypical Argyll-Robertson pupil.
Senile degeneration of the brain is a type of cerebral degeneration and also falls under the category of diseases that are located in the cerebrum. It is exactly synonymous with Senile brain degen.

Reye syndrome is a type of syndrome characterized by acute brain damage and liver function problems. It has been associated with aspirin consumption by children with viral illness, although it also occurs in the absence of aspirin use. Reye syndrome has the exact synonym Reye's syndrome.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:external_pathological_resorption rdfs:subClassOf :tooth_resorption .
text: external pathological resorption is a type of tooth resorption.
Atrophic glossitis is a type of glossitis and it has several exact synonyms including Atrophy of tongue papillae, Glossitis, Hunter's, Hunter's glossitis, and smooth atrophic tongue.
Malignant cardiac peripheral nerve sheath neoplasm is a type of malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumor and has the exact synonym MPNST of Heart.

Malignant cardiac germ cell tumor is a type of heart cancer and has several exact synonyms. These synonyms include malignant cardiac germ cell tumour, malignant germ cell tumor of the heart, and malignant germ cell tumour of the heart.

Rete testis adenocarcinoma is a type of adenocarcinoma and also a form of rete testis neoplasm. It falls under the category of diseases located in the rete testis and is characterized by being a type that intersects with epithelial cells and originates from glands. Rete testis adenocarcinoma is defined as a rete testis neoplasm that derives from epithelial cells of glandular origin. It is exactly synonymous with adenocarcinoma of the rete testis and is also relatedly known as adenocarcinoma of rete testis.

Seminal vesicle adenocarcinoma is identified as a type of adenocarcinoma and falls under the category of male reproductive organ cancer. It is characterized by its origin, being a disease that arises from an intersection of epithelial cells and glands, specifically located in the seminal vesicle. Furthermore, seminal vesicle adenocarcinoma is defined as a male reproductive organ cancer that derives from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

Sphenoidal sinus cancer is the same as a type of cancer that intersects with diseases located in the sphenoidal sinus. It is a type of paranasal sinus cancer and has the exact synonyms "malignant tumor of Sphenoidal sinus" and "malignant tumor of sphenoid sinus."

Sphenoid sinus squamous cell carcinoma is a type of cancer specifically affecting the sphenoidal sinus and is classified under squamous cell carcinoma. It originates from squamous epithelial cells and is characterized by its location in the sphenoidal sinus. This condition is defined as a squamous cell carcinoma located in the sphenoid sinus and is also exactly known as Epidermoid carcinoma of the Sphenoidal sinus.
Steroid-induced glaucoma borderline is a type of borderline glaucoma, which is exactly synonymous with Borderline glaucoma steroid responder and Steroid responders borderline glaucoma.

Geographic tongue is a type of atrophic glossitis and is defined as an inflammatory condition of the mucous membrane of the tongue, usually on the dorsal surface. It is also known by exact synonyms including Glossitis areata exfoliativa, Pityriasis linguae, and benign migratory glossitis.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:root_resorption rdfs:subClassOf :tooth_resorption .
text: root resorption is a type of tooth resorption.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:foster_kennedy_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :papilledema .
text: foster kennedy syndrome is a type of papilledema.

Primary pulmonary hypertension is a type of digenic disease and chronic pulmonary heart disease, which is characterized by having a material basis in some digenic inheritance. It exhibits symptoms such as syncope, dizziness, leg swelling, and dyspnea. Furthermore, primary pulmonary hypertension is defined as a chronic pulmonary heart disease characterized by an increase of blood pressure in the pulmonary artery, pulmonary vein, or pulmonary capillaries, among others, with symptoms including shortness of breath, dizziness, fainting, and leg swelling. It also has the exact synonym "Idiopathic pulmonary arterial hypertension."

:anaerobic_meningitis rdfs:subClassOf :bacterial_meningitis .
text: anaerobic meningitis is a type of bacterial meningitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:glossitis rdfs:subClassOf :tongue_disease .
text: glossitis is a type of tongue disease.

A disease of cellular proliferation is a type of disease characterized by abnormally rapid cell division and is also known by its exact synonyms, cell process disease and neoplasm. Additionally, it is identified by the OBI code 9991118 for neoplasm.
Postsurgical hypothyroidism, which is a type of hypothyroidism, is exactly synonymous with both Post-surgical hypothyroidism and Postoperative hypothyroidism.

Hypothyroidism is a type of thyroid gland disease and is defined as a thyroid gland disease which involves an underproduction of thyroid hormone. It is exactly synonymous with thyroid deficiency and thyroid insufficiency.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:papilledema rdfs:subClassOf :optic_nerve_disease .
text: papilledema is a type of optic nerve disease.
Atheroembolism of the kidney is a type of cholesterol embolism and a type of kidney disease. It is also a type of condition in which the disease is located in the kidney.

Cholesterol embolism is a type of vascular disease characterized by blood vessel obstruction resulting from the release of cholesterol from the inside of blood vessels along the bloodstream. It has several exact synonyms, including atheroembolism, cholesterol crystal embolism, purple toe syndrome, trash foot, and warfarin blue toe syndrome.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:prostatitis rdfs:subClassOf :prostate_disease .
text: prostatitis is a type of prostate disease.

Acrodysostosis is a type of dysostosis defined as a dysostosis that results in the shortening of interphalangeal joints, which are located in the hand or foot, and is accompanied by mental deficiency.

Serous labyrinthitis is a type of labyrinthitis defined as a labyrinthitis in which bacterial toxins invade the inner ear. This condition is the most common complication of acute or chronic middle ear infections. Moreover, serous labyrinthitis is exactly synonymous with acute serous labyrinthitis.

The Hypertelorism Microtia Facial Clefting Syndrome is a type of syndrome that is classified as an autosomal recessive disease and is characterized by the combination of hypertelorism, cleft lip and palate, and microtia. This syndrome is based on some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Bixler Christian Gorlin syndrome, Bixler syndrome, Bixler-Christian-Gorlin syndrome, HMC syndrome, Hypertelorism-Microtia-Clefting Syndrome, and Hypertelorism-microtia-facial clefting syndrome.

Multiple intestinal atresia is a type of autosomal recessive and intestinal disease that at least has a material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as an intestinal disease characterized by the presence of numerous atresic segments in the small and large intestines, which has its material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the TTC7A gene on chromosome 2p21. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms including GIDID, Multiple gastrointestinal atresias, familial intestinal polyatresia syndrome, and gastrointestinal defects and immunodeficiency syndrome.

VACTERL association is a type of syndrome, which is defined as a syndrome characterized by the presence of at least three of the following: vertebral defects, anal atresia, cardiac defects, tracheo-esophageal fistula, renal anomalies, and limb abnormalities. It is also related to the synonym VATER syndrome.

Labyrinthitis is a type of otitis interna and also falls under the category of conditions that have at least some inflammation as a symptom. It is defined as an otitis interna which involves inflammation of the labyrinths.

Silver Russell Syndrome is a type of physical disorder characterized by severe intrauterine growth retardation, poor postnatal growth, craniofacial features such as a triangular-shaped face and a broad forehead, body asymmetry, and a variety of minor malformations. It is also known exactly as Silver Russell Dwarfism.
Binder syndrome is a type of nasal cavity disease and is exactly synonymous with binder type maxillonasal dysplasia.

Axenfeld Rieger syndrome is a type of autosomal dominant and eye disease, which has its material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance and its location in the eye. It is characterized by abnormalities of the front part of the eye, known as the anterior segment. This syndrome is also exactly synonymous with Anomaly, Rieger's; Axenfeld syndrome; RGS - Rieger syndrome; and Rieger's anomaly. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Hagedoom syndrome.

Diastrophic dysplasia is an osteochondrodysplasia that is classified as a type of autosomal recessive disease and has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined by abnormal cartilage development due to mutations in the SLC26A2 gene, which results in short limb dwarfism.
Smith Lemli Opitz syndrome is a type of lipid metabolism disorder. It is also exactly known as Rutledge lethal multiple congenital anomaly syndrome and Smith-Opitz-Inborn syndrome.

Clouston syndrome, also known exactly as Clouston's hidrotic ectodermal dysplasia, Clouston's syndrome, Hidrotic ectodermal dysplasia syndrome, and ectodermal dysplasia 2, Clouston type, is a type of autosomal dominant disease and a form of ectodermal dysplasia. It is characterized by a specific condition that has its material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. The definition of Clouston syndrome highlights it as an ectodermal dysplasia characterized by abnormalities of the hair, nails, and skin, while the teeth and sweat glands remain unaffected. This condition has its material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the GJB6 gene, which encodes for connexin-30, located on chromosome 13q12.

Johanson Blizzard Syndrome (JBS) is a type of syndrome that is specifically an autosomal recessive disease. It is characterized by a condition that inherently has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. The syndrome involves abnormal development of the pancreas, nose, and scalp, alongside mental retardation, hearing loss, and growth failure, all of which are inherited in an autosomal recessive manner.

Galactokinase deficiency is a type of galactosemia and is defined as a galactosemia that involves an accumulation of galactose and galactitol secondary to the decreased conversion of galactose to galactose-1-phosphate by galactokinase. Additionally, galactokinase deficiency has the exact synonym Galactosemia II.

Thrombocytopenia absent radius syndrome is a type of syndrome that falls under the categories of autosomal recessive disease and chromosomal deletion syndrome. It is characterized by the absence of the radius bone and platelet deficiency, which includes bilateral absence of the radii while both thumbs remain present, and generally transient thrombocytopenia (less than 50 platelets/nL). This syndrome has its material basis in compound heterozygosity for a rare null mutation involving the RBM8A gene on chromosome 1q21.1 on one allele and one of two low-frequency noncoding single-nucleotide polymorphisms in RBM8A on the other allele. It is recognized by several exact synonyms, including Radial aplasia-thrombocytopenia syndrome, Thrombocytopenia with absent radii (TAR) syndrome, and chromosome 1q21.1 deletion syndrome. Furthermore, the disease's basis involves symptoms, indicating that it is partially defined by its manifestations.

Major depressive disorder is a type of depressive disorder that is characterized by at least two weeks of loss of interest or pleasure in normally enjoyable activities or depressed mood, alongside additional cognitive or somatic impairments. These impairments include appetite or weight changes, sleep difficulties, psychomotor agitation or retardation, fatigue or loss of energy, diminished ability to think or concentrate, feelings of worthlessness or excessive guilt, and suicidality. Furthermore, major depressive disorder is also known by several exact synonyms, including clinical depression, major depression, recurrent major depression, single major depressive episode, and unipolar depression.

Propionic acidemia is a type of organic acidemia characterized by a nonfunctional propionyl CoA carboxylase that affects the conversion of amino acids and fats into sugar for energy. It is also known by several exact synonyms including GLYCINEMIA, KETOTIC; KETOTIC HYPERGLYCINEMIA; ketotic II glycinemia; ketotic glycinemia; propionic aciduria; and propionyl-CoA carboxylase deficiency.

Branchiootorenal syndrome is a type of syndrome, specifically an autosomal dominant disease, with a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. It is characterized by branchial arch anomalies (branchial fistulas, clefts, or cysts), hearing impairment, structural defects of the outer, middle, and inner ear, and renal abnormalities. This syndrome is also known by exact synonyms such as Branchio-Oto-renal syndrome, Branchio-otorenal dysplasia, Melnick-Fraser syndrome, and branchiootorenal dysplasia.

Pfeiffer syndrome is an autosomal dominant disease and a type of acrocephalosyndactylia, which essentially has a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an acrocephalosyndactylia characterized by mutations in the FGFR1 and FGFR2 genes, leading to a premature fusion located in the skull. Additionally, Pfeiffer syndrome is exactly synonymous with acrocephalosyndactylia type V.

FG syndrome is a type of syndrome and a kind of X-linked recessive disease, which is something that has a material basis in some X-linked recessive inheritance. It is characterized by retardation, hyperactivity, hypotonia, broad thumbs, big first toes, and a distinctive facial appearance that includes macrocephaly, following an X-linked recessive inheritance pattern. Additionally, FG syndrome is exactly synonymous with Keller syndrome and Opitz-Kaveggia syndrome.

Centronuclear myopathy is a type of congenital structural myopathy, which is defined as a congenital structural myopathy characterized by abnormally located nuclei in skeletal muscle cells. In this condition, the nuclei are located in the center of the cell, instead of their normal location at the periphery. Furthermore, centronuclear myopathy has an exact synonym, myotubular myopathy.

Ehlers Danlos Syndrome Classic Type 1 is a type of Ehlers Danlos Syndrome and is also recognized as a form of autosomal dominant disease, specifically one that has a material basis in some form of autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome characterized by loose-jointedness and fragile, bruisable skin that heals with peculiar 'cigarette-paper' scars. This condition has its material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the collagen alpha-1(V) gene (COL5A1) on chromosome 9q34. Additionally, Ehlers Danlos Syndrome Classic Type 1 is exactly synonymous with both Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome, Type 1 and Type I Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome.

Beta ketothiolase deficiency is a type of autosomal recessive disease and an amino acid metabolic disorder that notably has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. This condition is characterized by an inability to process isoleucine and ketones, leading to recurrent ketoacidotic attacks in infancy, which are marked by symptoms such as vomiting, lethargy, dehydration, and seizures. The disorder originates from a mutation in the ACAT1 gene located on chromosome 11q22.3, which is essential for producing the ACAT1 enzyme in mitochondria that processes isoleucine and ketones. Additionally, beta ketothiolase deficiency is also known by several exact synonyms, including 2-methyl-3-hydroxybutyricacidemia, 3-ketothiolase deficiency, 3-oxothiolase deficiency, Mitochondrial acetoacetyl-CoA Thiolase deficiency, alpha-methylacetoaceticaciduria, and peroxisomal thiolase deficiency.

Autosomal dominant microcephaly is a type of autosomal dominant disease and a type of microcephaly, which falls under the category of conditions that at least have a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as a microcephaly that has its material basis in a heterozygous mutation in an autosomal gene.

Weaver syndrome is a type of syndrome that falls under the category of autosomal dominant diseases and is something that has its material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome characterized by prenatal and postnatal overgrowth, accelerated osseous maturation, distinctive craniofacial appearance, and developmental delay, which is caused by a heterozygous mutation in the EZH2 gene on chromosome 7q36. Additionally, Weaver syndrome is exactly synonymous with WEAVER-LIKE SYNDROME and Weaver-Williams syndrome.

Hereditary angioedema is a type of autosomal dominant disease and angioedema, which essentially has a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an angioedema characterized by recurrent episodes of severe swelling of the skin and mucous membranes. Hereditary angioedema is also known by its exact synonyms, HANE and Hereditary angioneurotic edema. Furthermore, it has exact matches with several medical databases, including MESH (D054179), OMIM (PS106100), and ORDO (91378).

Craniofrontonasal syndrome is a type of syndrome that falls under the category of X-linked dominant diseases, and it involves a condition that essentially has a material basis in X-linked dominant inheritance. This syndrome is defined by a mutation in the EFNB1 gene located on chromosome Xq13, characterized in hemizygous males by features such as hypertelorism, and exhibits with greater severity in females symptoms including frontonasal dysplasia, craniofacial asymmetry, craniosynostosis, bifid nasal tip, grooved nails, wiry hair, and abnormalities of the thoracic skeleton. Additionally, craniofrontonasal syndrome is known by several exact synonyms: CFND, CFNS, craniofrontonasal dysostosis, and craniofrontonasal dysplasia.

Aggressive periodontitis is a type of periodontitis that is defined as a periodontitis characterized by rapid attachment loss and bone destruction in the presence of little local factors such as dental plaque and dental calculus, resulting in inflammation and a loss of periodontium. It is exactly synonymous with juvenile periodontitis and has an exact match with MESH:D010520.

Trichorhinophalangeal syndrome type I is a type of syndrome, specifically an autosomal dominant disease. It has a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. This syndrome is characterized by several distinct features including short stature, sparse hair, a bulbous nasal tip, cone-shaped epiphyses, and severe generalized shortening of all finger and toe bones (brachydactyly). It is also known by exact synonyms such as trichorhinophalangeal syndrome type 1 and type I trichorhinophalangeal syndrome, with a related synonym being Trichorhinophalangeal dysplasia type I.

Partington syndrome is a type of syndromic X-linked intellectual disability, which is also a type of X-linked recessive disease, indicating that it at least has a material basis in some X-linked recessive inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome characterized by intellectual disability, focal dystonia of the hands, and dysarthria. Furthermore, Partington syndrome has an exact synonym: X-linked Russell-Silver syndrome.

Sotos syndrome is a type of autosomal genetic disease and a type of syndrome that has a material basis in some autosomal inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome that occurs rarely and is characterized by excessive physical growth during the first 2 to 3 years of life. Additionally, Sotos syndrome is exactly synonymous with cerebral gigantism.

Methylmalonic acidemia is a type of organic acidemia and is defined as an organic acidemia that involves an accumulation of methylmalonic acid in the blood. Additionally, it has the exact synonym methylmalonic aciduria.

Lymphangioma is a type of benign vascular tumor that is defined as a benign vascular tumor composed of dilated lymphatic channels. It has exact synonyms including Congenital lymphangioma and benign lymphangioma.

Isovaleric acidemia is a type of organic acidemia and is defined as an organic acidemia that disrupts or prevents normal metabolism of the branched-chain amino acid leucine. It has exact synonyms including Isovaleryl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency, isovaleric acid CoA dehydrogenase deficiency, and isovaleric aciduria.

Argininosuccinic aciduria is a type of amino acid metabolic disorder characterized by the accumulation of argininosuccinic acid (ASA) in the blood and urine. It is exactly synonymous with several terms including Argininosuccinate lyase deficiency, argininosuccinic acidemia, arginosuccinase deficiency, and deficiency of argininosuccinate lyase.

Vascular type Ehlers-Danlos syndrome (EDS) is a type of Ehlers-Danlos syndrome and an autosomal dominant disease, which specifically is a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. This particular syndrome is defined as an Ehlers-Danlos syndrome that has its material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the COL3A1 gene located on chromosome 2q32. It is characterized by the association of unexpected organ fragility, including arterial, bowel, and gravid uterine rupture, along with inconstant physical features such as thin, translucent skin, easy bruising, and acrogeric traits. Additionally, vascular type Ehlers-Danlos syndrome is exactly synonymous with autosomal dominant type IV Ehlers-Danlos syndrome.

Ehlers Danlos Syndrome Hypermobility Type is a type of Ehlers Danlos Syndrome, characterized by joint hyperextensibility without skeletal deformity. It is exactly synonymous with Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, type 3, and type III Ehlers-Danlos syndrome.

Autosomal recessive type IV Ehlers-Danlos syndrome is a type of Ehlers-Danlos syndrome and also falls under the broader category of autosomal recessive diseases. It is characterized by a type of condition that inherently has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. This particular syndrome is defined by the association of unexpected organ fragility, including arterial, bowel, and gravid uterine rupture, with inconstant physical features such as thin, translucent skin, easy bruising, and acrogeric traits. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, recessive type 4.

Greig cephalopolysyndactyly syndrome is categorized as a type of autosomal dominant disease, acrocephalosyndactylia, and is characterized by having a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an acrocephalosyndactylia that originates from mutations in the GLI3 gene, leading to abnormal development in the limbs, head, and face. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with polysyndactyly associated with a peculiar skull shape.

Calcaneonavicular coalition is a type of synostosis characterized by the fusion of carpal and tarsal bones, leading to stiffness and immobility of the hands and the feet. It is exactly synonymous with Multiple synostosis syndrome and SYNOSTOSES, TARSAL, CARPAL, AND DIGITAL.

Larsen syndrome is a type of syndrome, specifically an autosomal dominant disease, which means it is a condition that at least has a material basis in some form of autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance of large-joint dislocations and characteristic craniofacial abnormalities. Larsen syndrome is also exactly synonymous with dominant Larsen syndrome.

Renal agenesis is a type of kidney disease that is defined as a renal disease characterized by the failure of one or both kidneys to develop. It has several exact synonyms, including hereditary renal aplasia, hereditary urogenital adysplasia, renal adysplasia, and renal aplasia.

Saethre-Chotzen syndrome is a type of autosomal dominant disease and acrocephalosyndactylia, which stems from an autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an acrocephalosyndactylia that originates from a genetic mutation in the TWIST1 gene, leading to premature fusion in the skull. Additionally, Saethre-Chotzen syndrome is synonymously related to acrocephalosyndactyly type III.

Cartilage hair hypoplasia (CHH), also known as McKusick type metaphyseal chondrodysplasia or Metaphyseal chondrodysplasia, McKusick type, is a type of autosomal recessive disease, ectodermal dysplasia, and something that at least has a material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is characterized by short-limbed short stature and fine, sparse hair, with its material basis being homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the RMRP gene on chromosome 9p13.3.

Brittle Cornea Syndrome 1 is a type of disease that falls under several categories: it is an autosomal recessive disease, a corneal disease, and a variation of Ehlers Danlos Syndrome. This condition specifically has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance and is located in the cornea. It is characterized by blue sclerae, corneal rupture after minor trauma, keratoconus or keratoglobus, hyperelasticity of the skin, and hypermobility of the joints, with this condition being due to homozygous mutation in the ZNF469 gene on chromosome 16q24. Additionally, Brittle Cornea Syndrome 1 is exactly synonymous with Type VIB Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome.
Benign familial neonatal epilepsy is a type of neonatal period electroclinical syndrome and has the exact synonym "familial neonatal seizures."

Blepharophimosis ptosis and epicanthus inversus syndrome is a type of syndrome and an autosomal genetic disease that has its material basis in some form of autosomal inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis, epicanthus inversus, and telecanthus, with type I involving premature ovarian failure or without it. This condition has a material basis in heterozygous or rarely homozygous mutation in the FOXL2 gene on chromosome 3q22.3. Furthermore, it is also related to the synonym Blepharophimosis, ptosis, epicanthus inversus syndrome.

KBG syndrome is a type of spinal disease and a type of syndrome that affects various parts of the body. It is associated with diseases that are located in the vertebral column and the limbs. KBG syndrome is defined as a syndrome characterized by short stature, moderate to severe degrees of mental retardation, and developmental abnormalities of the limbs, bones of the spine (vertebrae), extremities, and/or underdevelopment of the bones of the skeleton.

Olivopontocerebellar atrophy is a type of neurodegenerative disease that is defined as a neurodegenerative disease characterized by progressive cerebellar ataxia. This leads to clumsiness in body movements, veering from the midline when walking, a wide-based stance, and falls without signs of paralysis or weakness. The material basis of this disease is the expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) resulting in the degeneration of neurons in the cerebellum, pons, and inferior olives. Olivopontocerebellar atrophy is also exactly synonymous with Dejerine-Thomas syndrome, Thomas' syndrome, and Wadia-Swami syndrome.

Spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia congenita is a type of autosomal dominant disease and a form of spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia that arises from autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as a spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia characterized by disproportionate short stature (short trunk), abnormal epiphyses, and flattened vertebral bodies, which results from a heterozygous mutation in the COL2A1 gene on chromosome 12q13.11. Additionally, spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia congenita is also known by its exact synonym, Late Spondyloepiphyseal Dysplasia.

Leber congenital amaurosis (LCA) is a type of physical disorder, specifically a retinal disease. It is classified under diseases that have their basis in some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. LCA is defined as a retinal disease characterized by nystagmus, sluggish or no pupillary responses, and severe vision loss or blindness. It is also known by exact synonyms such as LCA, Leber's amaurosis, Leber's congenital amaurosis, and Leber's disease.

Hypohidrotic ectodermal dysplasia is a type of ectodermal dysplasia that is characterized by malformations of ectodermal structures, including the skin, hair, teeth, and sweat glands. This includes hypotrichosis, which is the sparseness of scalp and body hair, hypohidrosis, referring to the reduced ability to sweat, and hypodontia, the congenital absence of teeth.

Dubowitz syndrome, also known exactly as Dubowitz's syndrome, is a type of syndrome that falls under the category of autosomal recessive diseases. It has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance and is characterized by specific phenotypes including retrognathia and growth delay, as well as symptoms like ptosis. The syndrome is defined by its unique characteristics, which include microcephaly, growth retardation, a distinctive facial appearance that may consist of a narrow or triangular-shaped head, micrognathia, ptosis, a broad, wide-tipped nose, and wide-set eyes with drooping eyelids.

Blount's disease is a type of osteochondrodysplasia and has the definition of an osteochondrodysplasia that results in the inward turning of the lower leg, located in the tibia, which fails to develop normally. Furthermore, Blount's disease is exactly synonymous with Blount disease and familial infantile type osteochondrosis deformans tibiae.

Gingival disease is a type of periodontal disease, which is a condition that is located in the gums. This disease is also known as gum disease. Additionally, it is defined as a periodontal disease that occurs in the gingiva.

Cystic fibrosis (CF), also known as mucoviscidosis, is a type of autosomal recessive disease and syndrome. It has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance and specifically, it has a unique material basis identified by the code "nf8b9e792c1304dbe89b040686ad1373e" which is associated with a loss of function variant located in a single gene disease. Cystic fibrosis is characterized by the buildup of thick, sticky mucus that can damage many organs. It is precisely matched with the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) identifier D003550.

Cystic echinococcosis is a type of echinococcosis that is characterized by affecting various parts of the body, including the bones, heart, liver, lungs, and brain. This disease is notable for having a range of symptoms such as urticaria, shock, hemoptysis, cough, abdominal mass, and anaphylactic shock. It is defined as an echinococcosis caused by the larvae of Echinococcus granulosus, which can lead to various complications including hepatic involvement resulting in abdominal pain, a hepatic area mass, biliary duct obstruction, pulmonary involvement with chest pain, cough, hemoptysis, fever, urticaria, eosinophilia, anaphylactic shock upon cyst rupture, and the possibility of cyst dissemination. Additionally, infections can occur in the brain, bones, and heart. 

Cystic echinococcosis is also known by several exact synonyms reflecting its diversity in infection sites and manifestations. These synonyms include Echinococcus granulosus infection, Echinococcus granulosus infection of lung, Echinococcus granulosus infection of thyroid, Liver echinococcus granulosus, Thyroid echinococcus granulosus, echinococcus granulosus, echinococcus granulosus infectious disease, echinococcus granulosus infectious disease of liver, echinococcus granulosus infectious disease of thyroid, lung echinococcus granulosus, unilocular echinococcosis, and unilocular hydatid disease.

Echinococcosis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, which is fundamentally based on the echinococcus. It is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of humans and domestic animals, caused by the larval stages of tapeworms of the genus Echinococcus, affecting the liver, lungs, spleen, brain, heart, and kidneys. Echinococcosis is precisely synonymous with several terms, including Echinococcosis of liver, echinococcal disease, hepatic echinococcosis, hydatid disease, hydatidosis, liver echinococcus, and pulmonary echinococcosis.

Cholera is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease with a material basis in Vibrio cholerae. It is transmitted through vehicle-borne ingestion and has symptoms such as shock, diarrhea, and vomiting. Cholera is defined as an acute, diarrheal illness caused by infection of the intestine with the bacterium Vibrio cholerae, characterized by profuse watery diarrhea, vomiting, leg cramps, circulatory collapse, and shock. It has exact synonyms including "Cholera - Vibrio cholerae," "Cholera due to Vibrio cholerae," and "Vibrio cholerae." Additionally, cholera has an exact match with MESH:D002771.

A reproductive system disease, which is also known as a genital system disease, is defined as a disease of an anatomical entity that is located in the reproductive system organs. It is characterized as a type of disease of an anatomical entity that shares the commonality of being a disease located in the reproductive system. This encompasses anything that is a disease and is found within the reproductive system.

A disease of mental health is a type of disease characterized by a psychological or behavioral pattern that generally involves subjective distress or disability occurring in an individual. These patterns are not considered part of normal development or culture.

Candidiasis is a type of opportunistic mycosis and also a type of condition that has a material basis in some Candida species. It is defined as an opportunistic mycosis that involves fungal infection of various body parts including the mouth, throat, skin, scalp, vagina, fingers, nails, bronchi, lungs, heart, and brain by Candida species, with Candida albicans being the most common. Moreover, Candidiasis has exact synonyms: Disseminated candidiasis and systemic candidiasis, indicating its broad impact on the body. Systemic Candida infections are typically confined to severely immunocompromised individuals.

Avoidant personality disorder is a type of personality disorder characterized by a pervasive pattern of social inhibition, feelings of inadequacy, extreme sensitivity to negative evaluation, and avoidance of social interaction. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with anxious personality disorder.

Personality disorder is a type of mental health disease characterized by long-term patterns of thoughts and behaviors that cause serious problems with relationships and work. It is also exactly synonymous with character disorder.

Chronic gonorrhea of the cervix is a type of chronic cervicitis, which is defined as a chronic cervicitis caused by gonorrhea. It has exact synonyms including Gonococcal cervicitis, chronic, and chronic gonococcal cervicitis.
Chronic cervicitis is a type of cervicitis defined as a cervicitis that is present for weeks or more.

Cecal benign neoplasm is defined as an intestinal benign neoplasm located in the cecum, which is the same as an entity that is both a benign neoplasm and a disease with its location in the caecum. It is identified as a type of cecal disease as well as a type of intestinal benign neoplasm. Furthermore, cecal benign neoplasm is exactly synonymous with both cecum neoplasm and neoplasm of caecum.

Cecal disease is the same as a disease that intersects with something that is at least a disease and has a location in the caecum. It is a type of intestinal disease and is defined as an intestinal disease located in the cecum. Additionally, cecal disease has the exact synonym "disorder of cecum."

Cecum carcinoma is a type of cecum cancer and also a subtype of carcinoma. It specifically falls into the category of cancers that intersect with conditions deriving from epithelial cells. The definition of cecum carcinoma is a cecum cancer that originates from abnormally proliferating cells, which are derived from epithelial cells. Furthermore, cecum carcinoma is exactly synonymous with several terms including Caecum carcinoma, Cecal cancer, and carcinoma of the cecum.

Colon carcinoma is a type of colon cancer and also a type of carcinoma. It is defined as a type of something that intersects something that is cancer and something that at least derives from some epithelial cell. Additionally, it is a type of something where the disease is located in the colon. Colon carcinoma is defined as a colon cancer that has a material basis in abnormally proliferating cells derived from epithelial cells. It has exact synonyms, including Colonic carcinoma and carcinoma of colon.

Cecum cancer, also known by its exact synonyms malignant neoplasm of caecum and malignant tumor of the cecum, is a type of cancer that intersects with diseases located in the caecum. It is classified both as a type of cecal disease and as a type of large intestine cancer. Specifically, cecum cancer is defined as a large intestine cancer located in the cecum.

Cecum lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of cecum cancer, characterized as something that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. It is also known by its exact synonym, Cecal Lymphoma.

Colon lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and also a type of colon cancer, which is characterized by something that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. Additionally, colon lymphoma is exactly synonymous with Colonic Lymphoma.

Nodular nonsuppurative panniculitis is a type of panniculitis. It has exact synonyms: Relapsing febrile nodular nonsuppurative panniculitis, Weber-Christian disease, and nodular non-suppurative febrile panniculitis.
Panniculitis is a type of skin disease, defined as a skin disease characterized by inflammation of subcutaneous adipose tissue.

Penile disease is equivalent to an intersection involving a condition that is a disease and something that, at a minimum, has a disease located in the penis. Additionally, penile disease is classified as a type of male reproductive system disease.

Pleural disease is defined as a thoracic disease that may involve inflammation of the pleura, collection of air within the pleural cavity, abnormal collection of pleural fluid, abnormal growths on the pleura (pleural tumor), and pleural plaques. The main causes of pleural diseases, including pleural effusions, are congestive heart failure, malignancy, parapneumonic infections, and pulmonary embolism. It is synonymous with disorders of the pleura and non-neoplastic pleural disease. Pleural disease is identified as the same as something that intersects with diseases having a location in the pleura. This condition is a type of lower respiratory tract disease and is characterized by symptoms such as inflammation and heart failure.

Mixed cell type cancer is equivalent to a condition arising from the intersection of cancer and a union of conditions derived from the intersection of cells originating from at least two different germinal layers: ectodermal and mesodermal cells, ectodermal and endodermal cells, as well as mesodermal and endodermal cells. This type of cancer is a specific category within cell type cancers. Furthermore, mixed cell type cancer is classified as a disease located in tissues originating from a union of intersections between ectoderm and endoderm, ectoderm and mesoderm, and endoderm and mesoderm. It is defined as a cell type cancer characterized by the abnormal proliferation of cells that are derived from two germinal layers of tissue.

In terms of terminology, mixed cell type cancer is precisely known as malignant mixed cancer, malignant mixed neoplasm, mixed tumor, and mixed tumor, malignant. Additionally, it is relatedly referred to as malignant mixed tumor and mixed neoplasm.

Parathyroid carcinoma is a type of carcinoma, endocrine gland cancer, and parathyroid gland disease. It is a specific kind of cancer that at least derives from some epithelial cell and has a location in the parathyroid glands. Parathyroid carcinoma is defined as an endocrine gland cancer located in the parathyroid glands in the neck. It is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Parathyroid gland neoplasm, carcinoma of Parathyroid gland, malignant neoplasm of parathyroid gland, malignant neoplasm of the Parathyroid, malignant tumor of parathyroid gland, neoplasm of parathyroid gland, parathyroid gland cancer, parathyroid neoplasm. Additionally, it has a related synonym, parathyroid gland adenocarcinoma.

Head and neck carcinoma is a type of head and neck cancer and is also considered a type of carcinoma. It specifically originates from or at least derives from some epithelial cell. The definition of head and neck carcinoma is a head and neck cancer that has its material basis in epithelial cells and is located in the upper aerodigestive tract, which includes the lip, oral cavity (mouth), nasal cavity, paranasal sinuses, pharynx, and larynx. Additionally, "carcinoma of the neck" is an exact synonym for head and neck carcinoma, and it also has a related synonym, "carcinoma of neck."

Vibratory urticaria is a type of physical urticaria, which is defined as a physical urticaria characterized by itching, reddish skin, and swelling within minutes of local exposure to dermal vibration. This condition has a material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the ADGRE2 gene located on chromosome 19p13.
Urticaria is a type of skin disease that is defined as a skin disease characterized by a skin rash notable for pale red, raised, and itchy bumps, located in the upper dermis.

Arthus reaction is a type of hypersensitivity reaction type III disease, which is also known by the exact synonyms Arthus phenomenon and Arthus type urticaria. It is characterized by local vasculitis and has symptoms such as pain, edema, hemorrhage, or necrosis. These symptoms are due to the deposition of antigen-antibody immune complexes in vascular or serosal walls. The Arthus reaction specifically has at least some hemorrhage, necrosis, and edema as its symptoms.

Hypersensitivity reaction type III disease is a type of hypersensitivity reaction disease, which is defined as a hypersensitivity reaction disease characterized by the accumulation of antigen-antibody immune complexes, causing an inflammatory response and injury. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with immune complex disease.

Angioedema is a type of skin disease that is characterized by one or more areas of well-demarcated, non-pitting edema of deep subcutaneous tissues. It has several exact synonyms including Angioneurotic oedema, Quincke's edema, angioneurotic edema, and giant urticaria.

Cognitive disorder, also known as cognitive disease, is a type of disease of mental health. It is defined as a disease that affects cognitive functions including memory processing, perception, and problem solving. Additionally, it is related to the term Organic Mental Disorder.

Chromoblastomycosis is a type of subcutaneous mycosis, defined as a chronic subcutaneous fungal infection characterized by nodular or verrucoid, ulcerated, or crusted skin lesions on exposed areas of skin. It is caused by Fonsecaea pedrosoi, Fonsecaea compacta, Cladophialophora carrionii, or Phialophora verrucosa. Histological examination of this infection reveals muriform cells, which have perpendicular septations, or thick-walled, dark-colored, rounded forms, described as resembling copper pennies, that are characteristic of this condition. Furthermore, chromoblastomycosis has the exact synonyms Chromomycosis and Mossy foot disease.

Dermatomycosis is a type of cutaneous mycosis, skin disease, and has material basis in some Ascomycota. It is also defined as a disease located in some zone of the skin. Specifically, it is a cutaneous mycosis that results in a fungal infection located in the skin or its appendages, with the material basis in Ascomycota fungi other than the dermatophytes.

Fungal infectious disease, also known by the exact synonym mycosis and related to the term mycoses, is defined as a type of disease caused by an infectious agent that results in infection. This infection has its material basis in fungi, which are capable of passing the resistance barriers of the human or animal body. Furthermore, fungal infectious disease is the same as an intersection of diseases that have at least some material basis in fungi.

Ectropion is a type of eyelid disease, which is exactly synonymous with Ectropion of eyelid and Everted margin.

text: spastic ectropion is a type of ectropion.
Normal pressure hydrocephalus is a type of communicating hydrocephalus and is also exactly synonymous with low pressure hydrocephalus.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:communicating_hydrocephalus rdfs:subClassOf :hydrocephalus .
text: communicating hydrocephalus is a type of hydrocephalus.

Alcohol use disorder is a type of substance abuse defined as a substance abuse that involves the recurring use of alcoholic beverages despite negative consequences. It is also exactly synonymous with ethanol abuse and alcohol abuse.

Rheumatic disease is a type of connective tissue disease and it is also a type of condition that affects some connective tissue. Additionally, rheumatic disease is defined as a musculoskeletal system disease that involves inflammation or pain in the muscles, joints, or fibrous tissue.
Limited scleroderma, which is a type of systemic scleroderma, is exactly synonymous with both Limited cutaneous systemic sclerosis and systemic sclerosis, limited.

Pulmonary systemic sclerosis is a type of systemic scleroderma and a type of lung disease. It is also identified as something that, at least in part, has its location in the lung. Furthermore, pulmonary systemic sclerosis is precisely synonymous with both lung disease with systemic sclerosis and lung involvement in systemic sclerosis.

Respiratory system disease is equated to illnesses that are both diseases and have their location within the respiratory system, which spans from the nasal sinuses to the diaphragm. Furthermore, it is categorized as a type of disease affecting anatomical entities. Additionally, it is defined as a disease of an anatomical entity located in the respiratory system.
Diffuse scleroderma is a type of systemic scleroderma and has exact synonyms of diffuse systemic sclerosis and systemic sclerosis, diffuse.

Laryngeal tuberculosis is a type of laryngitis, characterized as a specific condition of pulmonary tuberculosis that causes granulomatous lesions in the larynx due to inflammation triggered by mycobacteria. This condition leads to several symptoms including hoarseness, dysphagia, and granulomatous inflammation.

Acute Chest Syndrome is a type of lung disease characterized by various symptoms, including hypoxemia, pleuritic chest pain, tachypnea, fever, cough, and leukocytosis. It is defined as a lung disease involving a vasoocclusive crisis of the pulmonary vasculature seen in patients with sickle cell anemia. This crisis is typically initiated by a lung infection, leading to inflammation and loss of oxygen tension, which causes sickling of red cells and further vasoocclusion. Symptoms of the disease include fever, pleuritic chest pain, tachypnea, cough, hypoxemia, marked leukocytosis, and diffuse infiltrates on chest radiograph. Acute Chest Syndrome is also known as Acute Chest Syndrome in Sickle Cell Disease and has an exact match in the MESH database with the identifier D056586.

Rheumatic fever is a type of bacterial infectious disease that has a material basis in Streptococcus pyogenes. It is characterized by symptoms such as joint pain and fever, and it features diseases like choreatic disease. Rheumatic fever is defined as a connective tissue disease that develops from an antecedent Group A Streptococcal pharyngeal infection. It exhibits symptoms including carditis, polyarthritis, chorea, erythema marginatum, subcutaneous nodules, arthralgia, a prolonged PR interval, and fever. Furthermore, Rheumatic fever is exactly synonymous with ACUTE RHEUMATIC FEVER and RhF - Rheumatic fever, and it has an exact match with the Medical Subject Headings (MeSH) identifier D012213.

Thrombocytopenia due to platelet alloimmunization is a type of thrombocytopenia. It has exact synonyms including Auto-immune thrombocytopenia, Immune thrombocytopenia, and Thrombocytopenia Due to Immune Destruction.
Thrombocytopenia is a type of blood platelet disease, which is defined as a condition characterized by a low platelet count in the blood.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:renovascular_hypertension rdfs:subClassOf :renal_hypertension .
text: renovascular hypertension is a type of renal hypertension.

Melancholic depression is a type of major depressive disorder characterized by a near-complete absence of pleasure. It is also known by its exact synonyms: endogenous depression, major depressive disorder with melancholic features, and melancholia.

Depressive disorder is a type of mood disorder characterized by persistent sadness, emptiness, or irritability and decreased ability to function. It is also known as mental depression and is closely related to depression. In medical terminology databases, depressive disorder is matched exactly to MESH:D003866, NCI:C2982, and SNOMEDCT_US_2023_02_28:35489007, and has a close match with UMLS_CUI:C0011570.

The integumentary system disease is identical to an entity that is both a disease and is located in the integumentary system, which includes the skin and its appendages. Additionally, an integumentary system disease is categorized as a type of disease affecting anatomical entities. It is defined as a disease of an anatomical entity situated within the integumentary system.

Lymphadenitis is a type of lymph node disease that is characterized by an acute or chronic inflammation of one or more lymph nodes. It is also known by several exact synonyms including Adenitis, Inflammation of lymph node, acute adenitis, acute lymphadenitis, chronic Lymphadenitis, and chronic adenitis.

Hypoglycemic coma is classified as a type of brain disease that inherently has at least some cognitive impairment and symptoms including seizures and coma. Additionally, it is defined as a brain disease characterized by coma or unconsciousness, which develops due to a prolonged insufficient supply of glucose to the brain. This condition is associated with symptoms such as decreased cognition, seizures, and coma.
Keratosis is a type of skin disease that is defined as a skin disease characterized by the growth of keratin on the skin or mucous membranes.

Breast cancer is the same as something that is an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease, and it has a location in some part of the breast. It is a type of breast disease and also a type of thoracic cancer. Breast cancer is defined as a thoracic cancer that originates in the mammary gland. It has several exact synonyms, including breast tumor, malignant neoplasm of the breast, malignant tumor of the breast, mammary cancer, mammary tumor, and primary breast cancer. Additionally, breast cancer has a related synonym, which is mammary neoplasm.

Male breast cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease located at least in the male breast. It is a type of breast cancer defined as a breast cancer that occurs in males. Additionally, male breast cancer has exact synonyms, including "malignant neoplasm of male breast" and "neoplasm of male breast."

Benign eccrine breast spiradenoma is a type of breast benign neoplasm that arises from cutaneous sweat glands. It is characterized microscopically by two distinct cell populations: small, dark, basaloid cells with hyperchromatic nuclei, which are immunoreactive for P63 and calponin, and larger cells with a pale nucleus, often located near the center of the cluster (inner cells), which are immunoreactive for CK7 and CD117 (C-kit).

Breast fibroadenoma is defined as a type of breast benign neoplasm, which is also classified as an adenoma. It falls under a category that intersects entities deriving from epithelial cells and having an origin in some gland. The definition of breast fibroadenoma is a breast benign neoplasm comprised of fibrous and glandular tissues located in the breast. It has several exact synonyms, including Complex Fibroadenoma of Breast, Fibroadenoma of Breast, Juvenile Fibroadenoma, Cellular Fibroadenoma, Fibroadenoma, and Juvenile Fibroadenoma of Breast.

Cancer is a type of disease characterized by cellular proliferation. It is defined as a disease of cellular proliferation that is malignant and primary, characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation, local cell invasion, and metastasis. Additionally, cancer is exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm, malignant tumor, and primary cancer.
Breast leiomyoma is a type of breast benign neoplasm, defined as a breast benign neoplasm that has its material basis in smooth muscle cells.

Breast adenoma is a type of adenoma and a specific kind of breast benign neoplasm. It is categorized under entities that are derived from epithelial cells and have origins in glands. The definition of breast adenoma is a breast benign neoplasm that has its material basis in epithelial tissue, where tumor cells form glands or gland-like structures. Furthermore, breast adenoma is exactly synonymous with Ademoma - breast.

Breast duct papilloma is a type of intraductal papillary breast neoplasm, which is also a type of papilloma. It is categorized under entities that derive from both epithelial cells and mucosa. This condition is defined as an intraductal papillary breast neoplasm with a material basis in epithelial tissue on papillae of vascularized connective tissue. Additionally, breast duct papilloma is exactly synonymous with duct papilloma of the breast and papilloma of the breast.

Intraductal papilloma is a type of papilloma and an intraductal breast benign neoplasm, which at least derives from some epithelial cell and some mucosa. Furthermore, intraductal papilloma has the exact synonym ductal papilloma.
Intraductal papillary breast neoplasm is a type of intraductal breast benign neoplasm, which is defined as an intraductal breast benign neoplasm characterized by fingerlike growth projections.
Breast myofibroblastoma is a type of breast benign neoplasm and it is defined as a breast benign neoplasm that derives from precursor mesenchymal cells with myofibroblastic differentiation.

Benign breast phyllodes tumor is a type of breast benign neoplasm, defined as a breast benign neoplasm that has its material basis in epithelial and stromal tissue and derives from periductal stromal cells of the breast. It is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Cystosarcoma phyllodes, Phyllodes neoplasm, benign Phyllodes neoplasm, benign Phyllodes neoplasm of the breast, and benign cystosarcoma phyllodes.

Breast angiomatosis is a condition that is at the intersection of capillary disease and diseases that have a location in the breast, making it both a type of capillary disease and a type of breast disease. It is defined as a breast disease characterized by diffuse vascularity surrounding ducts and lobules without invasion, large irregular vascular spaces, and flat epithelium without atypia.

Central nervous system tuberculosis is classified in several ways: it is a type of extrapulmonary tuberculosis, a type of central nervous system disease, and a type of condition that has its location in some part of the central nervous system. It is defined as an extrapulmonary tuberculosis that results in the formation of tuberculomas located in the brain or spinal cord. Furthermore, central nervous system tuberculosis is also known by exact synonyms, including intracranial tuberculoma, tuberculoma of brain, tuberculosis of meninges and central nervous system, and tuberculous abscess of brain.

Skeletal tuberculosis is a type of extrapulmonary tuberculosis, a bone disease, and it is a condition where the disease has a location in some element of the bone. It is defined as an extrapulmonary tuberculosis that results in the formation of lesions located in the bone. Skeletal tuberculosis is also exactly synonymous with osteoarticular tuberculosis.

Benign breast adenomyoepithelioma is a type of breast benign neoplasm characterized by dual differentiation into luminal cells and myoepithelial cells. It is also exactly synonymous with benign adenomyoepithelioma of the breast.

Breast adenomyoepithelioma is a type of breast myoepithelial neoplasm, which is defined as a breast myoepithelial neoplasm that affects the breast and is characterized by biphasic proliferation of both epithelial and myoepithelial cells. It is also known by exact synonyms such as breast Adenomyoepithelioma with malignant Change and malignant adenomyoepithelioma of breast. Additionally, it has a related synonym, adenomyoepithelioma of the breast.

Female breast upper inner quadrant cancer is a type of female breast cancer, which is defined as a female breast cancer that is located in the upper-inner quadrant of the breast. Additionally, it has the exact synonym "malignant neoplasm of the upper-inner quadrant of the female breast."

Female breast lower inner quadrant cancer is a type of female breast cancer, which is defined as a female breast cancer located in the lower-inner quadrant of the breast. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: malignant neoplasm of the lower-inner quadrant of the female breast.

Female breast axillary tail cancer is a type of female breast cancer and is defined as a female breast cancer that is located in the breast tissue extending into the axilla. It has the exact synonym "malignant neoplasm of axillary tail of female breast."

Ventricular septal defect is synonymous with an entity that is both a heart disease and a disease that occurs in the interventricular septum. It is a specific type of heart septal defect characterized by an opening in the interventricular septum, which leads to a shunt between the ventricles. Additionally, ventricular septal defect is exactly referred to as interventricular septal defect and ventricular septal abnormality.

Supratentorial cancer is a type of brain cancer characterized by its location in the supratentorial region. It is precisely defined as a brain cancer situated in this area. This condition is also exactly synonymous with "Brain neoplasm, Supratentorial" and "malignant Supratentorial tumor."

text: Melanotic neuroectodermal tumor is a type of bone benign neoplasm, which has several exact synonyms. These include Infantile Melanotic neuroectodermal neoplasm, Melanotic neuroectodermal tumor of infancy, Melanotic neuroectodermal tumour of infancy, Pigmented neuroectodermal tumour of infancy, and melanotic neuroectodermal tumour.

Malignant pineal area germ cell neoplasm is a type of pineal gland cancer, which has exact synonyms including Pineal Region germ cell tumor, malignant Pineal Parenchymal germ cell tumor, and pineal germ cell tumor.
Pineoblastoma is a type of pineal gland cancer and is defined as a pineal gland neoplasm located in the brain. It also has an exact synonym, Pineal PNET.
