text: Behcet's syndrome arthropathy is a type of arthropathy. It has exact synonyms that describe its involvement in various body parts: Arthropathy in Behcet's syndrome involving the ankle and foot, forearm, hand, lower leg, multiple sites, pelvic region and thigh, shoulder region, and upper arm. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Behcet syndrome arthropathy.

Spontaneous tension pneumothorax is a type of pneumothorax defined as a pneumothorax characterized by a situation in which the pressure of intrapleural gas exceeds atmospheric pressure, resulting in acute onset chest pain and shortness of breath.

Pneumothorax is a type of pleural disease and is defined as a pleural disease characterized by an abnormal collection of air in the pleural space between the lung and the chest wall. Additionally, it has an exact match with MESH:D011030.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:low_implantation_of_placenta rdfs:subClassOf :placenta_praevia .
text: low implantation of placenta is a type of placenta praevia.

Chronic interstitial cystitis is a type of chronic cystitis and it is characterized by an unpleasant sensation related to the bladder and lower urinary tract in the absence of identifiable causes. It manifests with symptoms such as pain, pressure, discomfort, dysuria (painful urination), and/or urinary frequency. Additionally, chronic interstitial cystitis is acknowledged for having at least the symptoms of some pain and dysuria.
Cystitis is a type of bladder disease and is characterized by inflammation of the bladder, making it a condition that at least has some inflammation as a symptom.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_cystitis rdfs:subClassOf :cystitis .
text: chronic cystitis is a type of cystitis.

A heart septal defect is defined as the intersection of conditions categorized under heart disease and those diseases that have their location specifically in the cardiac septum. It is a type of congenital heart disease. Additionally, this condition is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Cardiac septal defects, Congenital septal defect of heart, and simply septal defect.

Congenital heart disease is a type of physical disorder, specifically a heart disease, that has its basis in some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. It is exactly synonymous with Congenital Heart Defects, Congenital anomaly of heart, Heart Malformation, congenital heart defect, and heart defect. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Heart-congenital defect.

Glaucoma is a type of eye disease, defined as an eye disease characterized by an unstable or a sustained increase in the intraocular pressure which the eye cannot withstand without damage to its structure or impairment of its function.

Neovascular glaucoma is a type of glaucoma that is characterized by the narrowing of the anterior chamber angle due to neovascularization along the iris and iridocorneal angle, which obstructs the outflow of aqueous fluid, leading to elevated intraocular pressure, optic nerve damage, and visual field loss. This condition is associated with symptoms including progressive peripheral vision loss, decreased vision, pain, redness, and headache in acute cases. Additionally, it exhibits symptoms such as some pain, loss of vision, bloodshot eye, and headache. Neovascular glaucoma has features like ocular hypertension and is related to abnormal angiogenesis with underlying causes like ischemic retinal diseases, inflammation, diabetes mellitus, intraocular malignancy, and autoimmune diseases. It is also known by the exact synonym "secondary angle-closure glaucoma with rubeosis."

A neuroendocrine tumor is a type of endocrine gland cancer, which is defined as an endocrine gland cancer that has its material basis in neuroendocrine cells. This condition is also exactly synonymous with neuroendocrine neoplasm.

Ichthyosis is a type of skin disease and is also a type of condition that involves at least some epidermal thickening as part of its phenotype. It is defined as a skin disease characterized by drying and scaling of the skin with the accumulation of thick scales and cracks that may be painful or bleed. Furthermore, ichthyosis has exact synonyms, including "ichthyoses" and "non-syndromic ichthyosis."

A musculoskeletal system disease is the same as a disease that intersects with a condition that is located at least partially within the musculoskeletal system. It is a specific type of disease that affects anatomical entities. Moreover, the definition of a musculoskeletal system disease is a disease of an anatomical entity that occurs in the muscular and/or skeletal system.

Endocrine gland cancer, which is the same as something that intersects cancer and at least one disease located in some endocrine gland, is a type of organ system cancer. It is defined as an organ system cancer located in the endocrine system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of the hormone-producing glands of the endocrine system. Endocrine gland cancer has several exact synonyms, including Endocrine tumor, endocrine neoplasm, malignant Endocrine tumor, malignant neoplasm of endocrine gland, malignant tumor of endocrine gland, neoplasm of endocrine gland, and neoplasm of the endocrine system.

X-linked ichthyosis is a type of ichthyosis and a type of X-linked recessive disease. It is also a condition that at least has a material basis in some X-linked recessive inheritance. This condition is characterized by a build-up of scales on the skin, typically on the back of the neck and trunk, resulting from skin cells that do not properly separate from the outermost surface of the skin. This condition has a material basis in an X-linked recessive mutation or deletion of the STS gene on chromosome Xp22. Furthermore, X-linked ichthyosis has exact synonyms: X-linked ichthyosis with steryl-sulphatase deficiency, X-linked placental steryl-sulphatase deficiency, and X-linked recessive ichthyosis.
Steroid inherited metabolic disorder is a type of lipid metabolism disorder, defined as a lipid metabolism disorder that involves defects in steroid metabolism.

Ichthyosis vulgaris is a type of ichthyosis and an autosomal dominant disease, which specifically has a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an ichthyosis that results from a heterozygous mutation in the filaggrin gene (FLG) on chromosome 1q21, characterized by the accumulation of dead skin cells in thick, dry scales on the skin's surface. Additionally, ichthyosis vulgaris is exactly synonymous with Dominant Congenital Ichthyosiform Erythroderma.
Richter's syndrome is a type of chronic lymphocytic leukemia and has the exact synonym Richter syndrome.
Neuroectodermal tumor, which is a type of nervous system cancer, has an exact synonym: primitive Neuroectodermal neoplasm.

Aortic valve stenosis is a type of aortic valve disease and falls under the category of conditions that exhibit the phenotype of abnormal aortic valve physiology. It is defined as an aortic valve disease characterized by the narrowing of the heart's aortic valve opening. Aortic valve stenosis is also precisely known as Aortic stenosis, Rheumatic aortic stenosis, and rheumatic aortic valve stenosis. Additionally, it has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) database with the identifier D001024.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:benign_shuddering_attacks rdfs:subClassOf :movement_disease .
text: benign shuddering attacks is a type of movement disease.
Clear cell acanthoma is a type of skin benign neoplasm, which has the exact synonym Pale (Clear cell) acanthoma.
Duodenal ulcer is a type of peptic ulcer disease and has exact synonyms including Curling Ulcer, Curling's ulcers, and Stress Ulcer.

Peritoneum cancer, which is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease located in the peritoneum, is a type of organ system cancer. It is defined as an organ system cancer that is located in the peritoneum. Additionally, peritoneum cancer is related to the synonyms "cancer of peritoneum" and "peritoneal neoplasm."
Partial retinal vein occlusion is a type of retinal vein occlusion. It is also exactly synonymous with Partial Retinal Vein Occlusion and Partial occlusion of retinal vein.

Retinal vein occlusion is identified as an intersection of conditions categorized under retinal vascular occlusion and diseases that specifically affect the central retinal vein. It is classified as a type of retinal vascular occlusion as well as a form of vein disease. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with the term "Occlusion, of retinal vein."

Retinal vascular occlusion is a condition that falls under the categories of retinal vascular disease, peripheral vascular disease, and is a type of disease that occurs specifically in the retina. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with "Retinal vasc. occlusion."
Eccrine sweat gland neoplasm is a type of sweat gland benign neoplasm and has exact synonyms Eccrine tumor and eccrine skin neoplasm.

Histoplasmosis is a type of primary systemic mycosis and also a type of condition transmitted by airborne transmission. It is characterized by symptoms such as loss of appetite, headache, cough, and muscle pain. Histoplasmosis is defined as a primary systemic mycosis that results in systemic fungal infection. It has its material basis in either Histoplasma capsulatum var capsulatum or Histoplasma capsulatum var duboisii. The transmission is through airborne spores and the symptoms include a nonproductive cough, headache, loss of appetite, and muscle pains.

Cryptosporidiosis is a type of coccidiosis as well as a form of intestinal disease that originates from a parasitic protozoan infection in the intestine of humans and various animals, which is caused by Cryptosporidium species. This disease is usually transmitted through contaminated water and food. It is characterized by symptoms such as dehydration, weight loss, abdominal pain, nausea, diarrhea, fever, and vomiting, indicating that the disease primarily affects the intestine but can also impact other digestive tract organs, the lungs, and conjunctiva. Individuals with compromised immune systems are particularly vulnerable to developing this infection. Furthermore, cryptosporidiosis is also known by exact synonyms such as Cryptosporidial gastroenteritis, Infection by Cryptosporidium, and Intestinal cryptosporidiosis, highlighting its association with the Cryptosporidium species and its significant impact on the gastrointestinal system.

A duodenal benign neoplasm is defined as an intersection of a benign neoplasm and a disease that is located at least in the duodenum. It is categorized as a type of duodenum disease and also as a type of small intestine benign neoplasm. Furthermore, duodenal benign neoplasm is exactly synonymous with both neoplasm of duodenum and neoplasm of the duodenum.

A small intestine leiomyoma is a type of leiomyoma and also a type of small intestine benign neoplasm. It is classified as something that at least derives from some smooth muscle cell. The definition of a small intestine leiomyoma is a small intestine benign neoplasm that is located in the small intestine. Furthermore, it has an exact synonym which is "leiomyoma, small Bowel."
Acanthoma is a type of squamous cell neoplasm and has an exact match with MESH:D049309.
Drug psychosis, a type of drug-induced mental disorder, is exactly synonymous with Drug-induced psychosis and Drug-induced psychotic disorder.

Conjunctival squamous cell carcinoma is a type of squamous cell carcinoma and also a type of conjunctival cancer that derives from squamous epithelial cells. It is characterized as a disease located in the conjunctiva. This form of cancer is defined as a conjunctival cancer marked by the abnormal growth of dysplastic squamous epithelial cells on the surface of the eye, originating from the conjunctiva and infiltrating beyond the epithelial basement membrane. Conjunctival squamous cell carcinoma is known by several exact synonyms, including Conjunctival Epidermoid carcinoma, invasive squamous cell carcinoma of the conjunctiva, ocular surface squamous neoplasia, and squamous cell carcinoma of the conjunctiva.

Squamous cell carcinoma is the same as something that is an intersection of something that is cancer and something that at least derives from some squamous epithelial cell. It is a type of carcinoma with a definition specifying that it is a carcinoma that derives from squamous epithelial cells. Squamous cell carcinoma has several exact synonyms, including epidermoid carcinoma, malignant squamous cell tumor, squamous carcinoma, squamous cell Epithelioma, and squamous cell cancer.

Vascular cancer is identical to a condition that intersects with being a type of cancer and a disease located in the vascular system. This type of cancer is classified under both cardiovascular cancer and vascular disease categories. It is defined as a cardiovascular cancer that is situated within the blood vessels. Vascular cancer is known by numerous exact synonyms, including Blood vessel tumor, Blood vessel tumors, Blood vessel tumour disorder, Haemangiomatous tumour, blood vessel neoplasm, leiomyosarcoma of the renal vein, malignant great vessel tumor, malignant tumor of pulmonary vein, malignant tumor of pulmonary artery, malignant vascular neoplasm, malignant vascular tumor, neoplasm of great vessel, pulmonary artery malignant neoplasm, pulmonary vein malignant neoplasm, renal vein leiomyosarcoma, vascular tissue neoplasm, and vascular tumors.
Malignant conjunctival melanoma is a type of conjunctival cancer, which is exactly synonymous with conjunctival melanoma and malignant melanoma of the conjunctiva.

Ocular melanoma is a type of ocular cancer and it is defined as an ocular cancer that has its material basis in melanocytes and is located in the eye. It is also exactly synonymous with eye melanoma, intraocular melanoma, and melanoma of the eye.

Mitral valve stenosis is a type of mitral valve disease and also falls into a category of conditions that at least have the phenotype of mitral stenosis. It is defined as a mitral valve disease characterized by the narrowing of the orifice of the mitral valve of the heart. Furthermore, Mitral valve stenosis is exactly synonymous with Mitral stenosis.

Facial nerve disease is the same as a condition that is both a disease and is located in the facial nerve, which is also described as having at least some disease located in the facial nerve. Furthermore, facial nerve disease is classified as a type of cranial nerve disease. Additionally, it is defined as a cranial nerve disease that is located in the facial nerve, specifically the seventh cranial nerve.
Facial hemiatrophy, which is a type of facial nerve disease, is also known exactly as Parry-Romberg Syndrome.

American histoplasmosis is a type of histoplasmosis characterized by being a systemic fungal infection. It has a material basis in Histoplasma capsulatum var capsulatum and is transmitted by airborne spores. This condition exhibits several symptoms including a nonproductive cough, headache, loss of appetite, and muscle pains. Moreover, it is noted for being transmitted through some form of airborne transmission and specifically manifests symptoms such as loss of appetite, headache, and muscle pain.

Cardiovascular cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease, with its location being within the cardiovascular system. It is a type of organ system cancer and also classified as a type of cardiovascular system disease. Moreover, cardiovascular cancer is defined as an organ system cancer that is located in the heart and blood vessels. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Cardiovascular tumors and cardiovascular neoplasm.
Facial nerve neoplasm is a type of glossopharyngeal nerve neoplasm and it has exact synonyms including neoplasm of facial nerve and tumor of facial nerve.
Melkersson Rosenthal syndrome is a type of facial nerve disease, which is exactly synonymous with Cheilitis granulomatosa of Mescher-Melkersson-Rosenthal and Melkersson's syndrome.

Cheilitis is a type of lip disease and is also categorized as a condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. It is defined as a lip disease characterized by the inflammation of the lips, which may include the perioral skin, the vermilion border, and the labial mucosa. Additionally, Cheilitis has an exact match with the MESH code D002613.

Factitious disorder, which is a type of mental health disease, is defined as a condition where symptoms are deliberately produced, feigned, or exaggerated in order to falsely demonstrate the presence of an illness. This disorder is also exactly known as Munchausen syndrome.

Conversion disorder is a type of somatoform disorder characterized by numbness, blindness, paralysis, or fits without a neurological cause. It is also known by its exact synonyms: Conversion Hysterical Neurosis, Conversion hysteria or reaction, and Hysterical neurosis, conversion type.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:toxic_megacolon rdfs:subClassOf :megacolon .
text: toxic megacolon is a type of megacolon.

Labyrinthine unilateral reactive loss is a type of labyrinthine dysfunction and is exactly synonymous with both Loss of labyrinthine reactivity, unilateral and Unilateral loss of labyrinthine reactivity.
Unilateral hyperactive labyrinth is a type of labyrinthine dysfunction and has exact synonyms including hyperactive labyrinth, unilateral, and hyperactive unilateral labyrinthine dysfunction.

Vascular disease is equivalent to an intersection of something that is a disease and something that has at least a disease located in the vascular system. It is a type of cardiovascular system disease and is defined as a cardiovascular system disease that primarily affects the blood vessels, including the arteries, veins, and capillaries that carry blood to and from the heart. Additionally, vascular disease is exactly synonymous with vascular tissue disease.

Thyroid cancer is defined as an endocrine gland cancer located in the thyroid gland, which is situated in the neck below the thyroid cartilage. It is characterized as the intersection of cancer and a disease that necessarily has its location in the thyroid gland, thereby making it a type of both endocrine gland cancer and thyroid gland disease. Furthermore, thyroid cancer is precisely known by various synonyms including Thyroid gland neoplasm, malignant neoplasm of thyroid gland, malignant tumor of thyroid gland, neoplasm of thyroid gland, thyroid gland cancer, and thyroid neoplasm.

Pituitary cancer is categorized as a type of endocrine gland cancer and is also recognized as a specific disease affecting the pituitary gland. This cancer is fundamentally defined as an endocrine gland cancer situated in the pituitary gland, which is located at the base of the brain. Additionally, pituitary cancer is synonymous with several terms, including Pituitary gland neoplasm, malignant Pituitary neoplasm, malignant tumor of the pituitary gland, neoplasm of the pituitary gland, pituitary gland cancer, and pituitary neoplasm. Essentially, these terms all refer to the same condition, highlighting the various ways it can be identified.
Adrenal rest tumor is a type of benign neoplasm occurring in endocrine organs and has an exact synonym, "Adrenal Rest neoplasm." Furthermore, it has an exact match with MESH ID D000314.

Pericarditis is a type of pericardium disease characterized by inflammation of the pericardium, and it has symptoms including chest pain. This condition not only falls under the category of pericardium diseases but also manifests symptoms such as inflammation and chest pain.

Peritoneal mesothelioma is a type of cancer that specifically affects the peritoneum, and it is classified as a squamous cell carcinoma. This type of cancer derives at least in part from mesothelial cells. It is defined as a peritoneum cancer that develops from cells of the mesothelium and is located in the peritoneum. Furthermore, peritoneal mesothelioma is also known by exact synonyms including Advanced Malignant Mesothelioma of Peritoneum, advanced malignant peritoneal mesothelioma, and malignant mesothelioma of the peritoneum.
Benign peritoneal mesothelioma, a type of peritoneal benign neoplasm, is exactly synonymous with Mesothelioma of Peritoneum.

Malignant mesothelioma is the same as something that is an intersection of cancer and something that is an intersection of something that at least derives from some epithelioid macrophage and something that at least has a disease located in some mesothelium. It is a type of cell type cancer and has a definition as a cell type cancer that has a material basis in mesothelial tissue, which develops from the thin layer of tissue that covers many of the internal organs. Moreover, malignant mesothelioma has exact synonyms, including Diffuse malignant Mesothelioma, advanced malignant mesothelioma, asbestos-related malignant mesothelioma, and malignant tumor of Mesothelium.

Peritoneal carcinoma is a type of carcinoma and a type of peritoneum cancer, which also qualifies as a type of entity that at least derives from some epithelial cell and is a type of disease that has its location in the peritoneum. It is defined as a peritoneum cancer that is located inside the abdomen. Additionally, peritoneal carcinoma has an exact synonym: primary peritoneal carcinoma.
Pancreas lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and also a type of pancreatic cancer that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. Additionally, it has the exact synonym "Lymphoma of pancreas."

Pancreatic cancer is defined as an intersection of cancer and a disease that has a location in the pancreas. It is a type of endocrine gland cancer and also classified as a pancreas disease. The definition of pancreatic cancer specifies it as an endocrine gland cancer located in the pancreas. Pancreatic cancer has several exact synonyms, including Ca body of pancreas, Ca head of pancreas, Ca tail of pancreas, malignant neoplasm of body of pancreas, malignant neoplasm of head of pancreas, malignant neoplasm of tail of pancreas, pancreas neoplasm, pancreatic neoplasm, and pancreatic tumor.

Malignant exocrine pancreas neoplasm is defined as a type of pancreatic cancer that is the same as something that intersects with both cancer and a disease located in the exocrine pancreas. It specifically arises from the epithelial cells of the exocrine pancreatic tissue. This condition is also exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of the exocrine pancreas, malignant tumor of exocrine pancreas, and malignant tumour of exocrine pancreas.

Pancreas sarcoma is a type of sarcoma, a type of pancreatic cancer, and a type of something that at least derives from some embryonic cell metazoa. It is defined as a pancreatic cancer that is located in the pancreas and arises from transformed cells of mesenchymal origin. Additionally, pancreas sarcoma has an exact synonym: sarcoma of the pancreas.

Pancreatic endocrine carcinoma is a type of islet cell tumor, defined as an islet cell tumor that has its material basis in epithelial cells. It is exactly synonymous with islet cell carcinoma, carcinoma of the endocrine pancreas, malignant neoplasm of the islets of Langerhans, and pancreatic neuroendocrine carcinoma.

An islet cell tumor is identical to an entity that represents the intersection of cancer and a disease, which is located in the islet of Langerhans. It is classified as a type of pancreatic cancer and is defined as a pancreatic cancer situated in the pancreatic islet cells. This tumor is interchangeably referred to by several exact synonyms, including Islet cell neoplasm, endocrine pancreas cancer, islet cell tumour, malignant pancreatic Endocrine tumor, malignant pancreatic Endocrine tumour, malignant tumor of endocrine pancreas, malignant tumour of endocrine pancreas, and pancreatic Endocrine neoplasm.

Urinary system disease is equivalent to the intersection of a disease and an entity where at least one disease is located in the renal system. It is a subtype of disease of anatomical entities and is defined as a disease of anatomical entities that is located in the kidney, ureter, bladder, and urethra. Furthermore, urinary system disease has exact synonyms, which include Non-neoplastic urinary tract disease and urinary tract disease.

Ossifying fibroma is a type of bone benign neoplasm and has the definition of being a bone benign neoplasm that is located in the mouth and results in an overgrowth of gingival tissue due to irritation or trauma. It has the exact synonym Fibro-osteoma and a related synonym, peripheral ossifying fibroma.
Neuroendocrine carcinoma is a type of carcinoma and also a type of entity that at least derives from some neuroendocrine cell. It is defined as a carcinoma that derives from neuroendocrine cells.

Neuritis is a type of neuropathy and it has an exact synonym, which is peripheral neuritis.

:reflex_sympathetic_dystrophy rdfs:subClassOf :complex_regional_pain_syndrome .
text: reflex sympathetic dystrophy is a type of complex regional pain syndrome.

Calcinosis is a type of calcium metabolism disease characterized by the formation of calcium deposits in any soft tissue. It is defined as a calcium metabolism disease that results from this process. Calcinosis is also exactly synonymized with both "Pathologically calcified structure" and "pathologic calcification."

:secondary_lacrimal_atrophy rdfs:subClassOf :lacrimal_apparatus_disease .
text: secondary lacrimal atrophy is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease.
Status epilepticus is a type of epilepsy and is exactly synonymous with Grand mal status.

Childhood absence epilepsy is a type of childhood electroclinical syndrome that begins in childhood, characterized by brief and frequent absence seizures in children with an age of onset between four and ten years. It is also known as petit mal seizure or pyknolepsy, and is related to absence seizure.

Epilepsy is a type of brain disease characterized by the occurrence of at least two unprovoked seizures resulting from a persistent epileptogenic abnormality of the brain that is able to spontaneously generate paroxysmal activity. This condition is typically manifested by sudden brief episodes of altered or diminished consciousness, involuntary movements, or convulsions. Epilepsy is also known by its exact synonyms, epilepsy syndrome and epileptic syndrome. In terms of medical classification, epilepsy exactly matches with ICD10CM code G40 and has narrower matches with ICD10CM codes G40.9 and G40.909.

Idiopathic generalized epilepsy is a type of epilepsy and has the exact synonym Generalised epilepsy. It is defined as an epilepsy syndrome characterized by generalized seizures with no apparent cause, which arise from many independent foci (multifocal epilepsies) or from epileptic circuits that involve the whole brain.
Urethral stricture is a type of urethral obstruction and it has an exact match with MESH:D14525.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:mononeuritis_multiplex rdfs:subClassOf :mononeuritis_of_upper_limb_and_mononeuritis_multiplex .
text: mononeuritis multiplex is a type of mononeuritis of upper limb and mononeuritis multiplex.

Diabetic ketoacidosis is a type of metabolic acidosis and is defined as a metabolic acidosis that is characterized by the shift of the acid-base status of the body toward the acid side, accompanied by the accumulation of ketone bodies in body tissues and fluids, resulting from uncontrolled diabetes mellitus. Moreover, diabetic ketoacidosis has exact synonyms such as DIABETES MELLITUS, KETOSIS-PRONE, and ketosis-prone diabetes mellitus.
Menkes disease is a type of metal metabolism disorder and it has several exact synonyms. These synonyms include COPPER TRANSPORT DISEASE, Menkes kinky-hair syndrome, and steely hair syndrome.

Bone cancer is equivalent to an intersection of conditions that are cancers and diseases with at least one instance having a location in the bone element. It is identified as a type of bone disease and also categorized under connective tissue cancer. Bone cancer is defined as a connective tissue cancer located in bone, characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation that destroys normal bone tissue. Furthermore, bone cancer is synonymous with several terms including CA - bone cancer, bone neoplasm, bone tumor, malignant bone neoplasm, malignant bone tumor, malignant neoplasm of bone, malignant osseous tumor, neoplasm of bone, and osseous tumor.
Mononeuritis of the upper limb is a type of both mononeuritis of the upper limb and mononeuritis multiplex. Furthermore, it has an exact synonym, Mononeuritis upper limb.
Cannabis dependence is a type of hallucinogen dependence and has a definition as a drug dependence that involves the continued use of cannabis despite problems related to the use of the substance.

Intrahepatic cholestasis is a type of cholestasis and is defined as a cholestasis characterized by an impairment of the bile flow caused by an obstruction located in the liver. Additionally, it has an exact synonym, which is neonatal intrahepatic cholestasis.

Cherubism is a type of autosomal dominant disease and a type of skin disease that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as a bone disease characterized by the replacement of bone in the jaws with fibrous tissue, leading to facial swelling. This condition has a material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the SH3BP2 gene on chromosome 4p16.3.

Mc Cune Albright Syndrome is a type of autosomal genetic disease and syndrome, which essentially has a material basis in autosomal inheritance. This syndrome is defined by its characteristics, which include polyostotic fibrous dysplasia, precocious puberty, and café-au-lait spots, and it has a material basis in spontaneous post-zygotic missense mutations at ARG201 or Gln227 of the GNAS gene during embryogenesis. It is exactly synonymous with fibrous dysplasia of bone, osteitis fibrosa disseminata, and polyostotic fibrous dysplasia. Additionally, Mc Cune Albright Syndrome has an exact match with the MESH identifier D005359.

Jaw cancer is the same as something that intersects with both cancer and at least one disease located in the jaw skeleton. It is a type of bone cancer and is defined as a bone cancer and jaw disease that is located in the jaw, resulting in a swollen jaw, numbness or a tingling sensation in the jaw, and an abnormal growth of the jaw bone. Jaw cancer has an exact synonym, which is "neoplasm of jaw," and a related synonym, "jaw neoplasm."
Skull cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease located in the skull, which also intersects with the category of bone cancer.

Giant cell reparative granuloma is a type of bone giant cell tumor and a type of something that at least has the phenotype of some granuloma. It has exact synonyms including central giant cell (reparative) granuloma, central giant cell granuloma, and central giant cell reparative granuloma of the jaw.

:chronic_rheumatic_pericarditis rdfs:subClassOf :pericarditis .
text: chronic rheumatic pericarditis is a type of pericarditis.

Impotence is a type of sexual dysfunction and is defined as a sexual dysfunction that is characterized by a persistent or recurrent inability to achieve or to maintain an erection during sexual activity. It is also known by its exact synonyms, sexual impotence and erectile dysfunction.
Sexual dysfunction is a type of male reproductive system disease characterized by disturbances in sexual desire or performance.

Atrial heart septal defect, also known exactly as atrial septal defect, atrioseptal defect, auricular septal defect, congenital atrial septal defect, interatrial septal defect, and interauricular septal defect, is a type of heart septal defect. It is defined as a heart septal defect located in the septum that separates the two atria of the heart. This condition is the same as something that falls at the intersection of heart disease and a disease that has its location in the interatrial septum.

Hepatitis C is a type of viral infectious disease that has its material basis in Hepacivirus hominis. This disease presents with symptoms such as joint pain, liver inflammation, loss of appetite, abdominal pain, nausea, jaundice, fever, vomiting, fatigue, and acholic stool. It is defined as a viral infectious disease that results in inflammation located in the liver, transmitted when blood from an infected person enters the body of an uninfected person. The infection is characterized by fever, fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, clay-colored bowel movements, joint pain, and jaundice. Hepatitis C is also known by several exact synonyms including NANBH (non-A, non-B hepatitis), Viral hepatitis C, chronic hepatitis C, hepatitis C infection, and hepatitis nonA nonB.

Viral hepatitis is a type of hepatitis, which is a type of viral infectious disease, and is characterized by having a material basis in some viruses. It is defined as a hepatitis that involves viral infection causing inflammation of the liver. Moreover, viral hepatitis is exactly synonymous with viral hepatitis with hepatic coma, animal viral hepatitis, and human viral hepatitis.

Optic nerve disease is the same as the intersection of a disease and something that, at the very least, has a location on cranial nerve II. It is a type of cranial nerve disease. Furthermore, optic nerve disease is defined as a cranial nerve disease that is located in the optic nerve. It also has exact synonyms, including disorder of the second nerve, optic nerve disorder, and optic neuropathy.

text: eczematous dermatitis of eyelid is a type of noninfectious dermatoses of eyelid.
Noninfectious dermatoses of the eyelid, which has the exact synonym Non-infected eyelid dermatoses, is a type of blepharitis.

Allergic contact dermatitis of the eyelid is a type of allergic disease, noninfectious dermatoses of the eyelid, and something that at least has symptoms of some allergic reaction and is located on the eyelid. It is defined as a noninfectious dermatoses of the eyelid characterized by eczema, pruritus, or erythematous vesicles or papules of the eyelids, and it has a material basis in a type IV hypersensitivity reaction to an allergen or irritant. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: Contact and allergic dermatitis of the eyelid.
Sigmoid neoplasm is a type of colonic benign neoplasm which has exact synonyms including neoplasm of the sigmoid colon and tumor of the sigmoid colon.

text: sigmoid disease is a type of colonic disease.

Vagina sarcoma is a type of sarcoma and also a type of vaginal cancer, which originates from some embryonic cell metazoa and is located in the vagina. It is defined as a vaginal cancer that has its material basis in connective tissue and is exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the vagina.
Malignant skin fibrous histiocytoma is a type of malignant dermis tumor and has exact synonyms such as malignant fibrous histiocytoma of skin and vaginal melanoma.
Malignant fibrous histiocytoma is a type of sarcoma that also has the exact synonyms Fibroxanthosarcoma and MFH.

Melanoma is identical to an intersection of something that is cancer and something that, at the very least, derives from melanocytes. It is a type of cell-type cancer with a definition as a cell-type cancer that is based on abnormally proliferating cells originating from melanocytes, which are located in the skin, the bowel, and the eye. Melanoma is precisely synonymous with Naevocarcinoma and malignant melanoma. Additionally, melanoma has an exact match with MESH:D008545.

Vaginal yolk sac tumor is a type of vaginal cancer characterized by being a primitive, malignant, germ cell tumor with histological features that recapitulate various development phases of the normal yolk sac. It is also known by its exact synonyms, vaginal Yolk Sac neoplasm and vaginal endodermal sinus neoplasm.

Endodermal sinus tumor is a type of germ cell cancer that is defined as a germ cell cancer with a material basis in cells that line the yolk sac of the embryo. It has several exact synonyms, including Hepatoid yolk sac tumour, Yolk Sac neoplasm, Yolk sac tumour, endodermal sinus tumour, infantile embryonal carcinoma, and yolk sac tumor.

Lesch-Nyhan syndrome is identified as a type of X-linked recessive disease and falls under the category of purine-pyrimidine metabolic disorders. It is recognized for having a material basis in some X-linked recessive inheritance. The syndrome is defined as a purine-pyrimidine metabolic disorder characterized by mental retardation, spastic cerebral palsy, choreoathetosis, uric acid urinary stones, and self-destructive biting of fingers and lips, which is caused by a mutation in the hypoxanthine guanine phosphoribosyltransferase (HPRT) gene located on chromosome Xq26. 

Lesch-Nyhan syndrome is known by several exact synonyms, which include Complete hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase deficiency, HG-PRT deficiency, Hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase deficiency (both forms with and without hyphens), Lesch - Nyhan syndrome, X-linked hyperuricemia, deficiency of IMP pyrophosphorylase, and hypoxanthine guanine phosphoribosyltransferase deficiency.

Sex cord-gonadal stromal tumor is a type of reproductive organ cancer that is characterized specifically by its location in the sex cord-derived tissues of the ovary or testis. It originates from various cells, including granulosa cells, Leydig cells, Sertoli cells, and fibroblasts. This condition is also known by several exact synonyms, including Sex Cord-Stromal neoplasm, Sex cord stromal tumour, Specialized gonadal neoplasm, Specialized gonadal tumor, Specialized gonadal tumour, and sex cord-gonadal stromal tumour.

Hyperuricemia is a type of acquired metabolic disease and it is defined as an acquired metabolic disease that has a material basis in an abnormally high level of uric acid in the blood. Additionally, hyperuricemia has exact synonyms including "Blood urate raised" and "uricacidemia."

Klinefelter syndrome is a type of chromosomal duplication syndrome characterized by infertility, with its material basis in an extra X chromosome in cells in men. It is precisely referred to by several synonyms including 47, XXY, Hypogonadotropic Hypogonadism, Klinefelter's syndrome, XXY syndrome, and XXY trisomy.

Disorder of sexual development is a type of gonadal disease and is defined as a gonadal disease characterized by atypical development of chromosomal, gonadal, or anatomic sex. It has exact synonyms, including sex development disorder and sex differentiation disease.
Hypogonadism is a type of gonadal disease and is defined as a gonadal disease characterized by diminished functional activity of the gonads.

Coffin-Siris syndrome is a type of syndrome that is specifically an autosomal dominant intellectual developmental disorder, characterized by mental retardation associated with coarse facial features, hypertrichosis, sparse scalp hair, and hypoplastic or absent fifth fingernails or toenails. This syndrome is equivalent to a condition that intersects with a syndrome and a disease located at digit 5. It also has exact synonyms, including Dwarfism-Onychodysplasia, Fifth Digit Syndrome, and Short Stature-Onychodysplasia.

Gaucher's disease is a type of sphingolipidosis characterized by a deficiency of the enzyme glucocerebrosidase, leading to the accumulation of harmful quantities of the glycolipid glucocerebroside throughout the body, especially within the bone marrow, spleen, and liver. It has several exact synonyms, including Gaucher disease, acid beta-glucosidase deficiency, glucocerebrosidase deficiency, glucosylceramide beta-glucosidase deficiency, and kerasin thesaurismosis.

Sphingolipidosis is a type of lipid storage disease that is defined as a lipid storage disease characterized by functional deficiencies in the enzymes needed for lysosomal degradation of sphingolipid substrates. It has an exact synonym, sphingolipidoses.

Williams Beuren Syndrome (WBS) is a syndrome characterized by a specific set of features, including mild to moderate intellectual disability, a broad forehead, a short nose with a broad tip, full cheeks, and a wide mouth with full lips, alongside difficulty with visual-spatial tasks. It is an autosomal dominant disease and also a chromosomal deletion syndrome, specifically caused by a hemizygous deletion of 1.5 to 1.8 Mb on chromosome 7q11.23. This syndrome exists at the intersection of conditions with a material basis in chromosome deletions and autosomal dominant inheritance. WBS is also known by its exact synonyms, Fanconi Schlesinger Syndrome and WBS.

Supravalvular aortic stenosis is a type of aortic valve stenosis and is defined as an aortic valve stenosis characterized by a narrowing of the section of the aorta just above the valve that connects the aorta to the heart. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: Supra-valvular aortic stenosis.

Reproductive organ cancer is a type of cancer that intersects with diseases located in the reproductive system, making it a specific type of both organ system cancer and reproductive system disease. It is defined as an organ system cancer that is manifested in the reproductive organs. This condition is also known by its exact synonyms, which include "Reproductive tumor" and "malignant reproductive system neoplasm." Additionally, it has a related synonym, "cancer of the reproductive system."

Laurence Moon Syndrome (LMS), which is also precisely known as LNMS and relatedly referred to as Laurence-Moon-Biedl syndrome, is a type of autosomal recessive disease and syndrome. It has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance and is specifically characterized by pituitary dysfunction, childhood onset ataxia, peripheral neuropathy, spastic paraplegia, and chorioretinopathy. This syndrome is caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutations in the PNPLA6 gene located on chromosome 19p13.2.

Hypothalamic disease is identical to an intersection of something that is a disease and something that has at least one disease located in the hypothalamus. Additionally, hypothalamic disease falls under the category of brain disease and is defined as a brain disease situated in the hypothalamus.

Angelman syndrome is a type of syndrome characterized by delayed development, intellectual disability, severe speech impairment, and problems with movement and balance. It is also known by the exact synonyms "happy puppet syndrome" and "puppetlike syndrome." The condition is associated with various genetic mechanisms including maternally imprinted genes and loss of function variants, paternal uniparental disomy, and chromosomal deletions involving gene(s) with a location linked to a single-gene disease. Specifically, it has a material basis in the loss of function variants, including those involving at least one gene identified by the identifier "nead9a61d0f1641c098db2cc1652d9fe9," maternal variants, and chromosomal deletions. Angelman syndrome also has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) under the identifier D017204.

Rubinstein Taybi Syndrome (RTS) is a type of syndrome that is characterized by various genetic and chromosomal factors. It is classified as an autosomal dominant disease and also falls under the category of chromosomal deletion syndrome. The genetic basis of RTS includes intersections involving at least some deletions and chromosomes, specifically pointing to its material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance and its link to chromosomal aspects. RTS is defined by distinct clinical features including short stature, moderate to severe intellectual disability, distinctive facial features, and broad thumbs and first toes. Furthermore, RTS is known by several exact synonyms, including Broad Thumb-Hallux syndrome, Rubinstein syndrome, and proximal chromosome 16p13.3 deletion syndrome.
Dysostosis is a type of bone development disease characterized by defective ossification of bone.

Bardet Biedl syndrome is a type of syndrome and an autosomal recessive disease that fundamentally has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome that arises from mutations in multiple BBS genes, which affect cellular cilia structure or function (ciliopathy). This results in a variable presentation and is primarily characterized by obesity, retinitis pigmentosa, vision loss, polydactyly, mental retardation, hypogonadism, and in some cases, renal failure.
Atherosclerosis is a type of arteriosclerotic cardiovascular disease and has an exact match with MESH:D050197.
Intermittent squint is a type of strabismus and has the exact synonym Intermittent heterotropia.

:telogen_effluvium rdfs:subClassOf :alopecia .
text: telogen effluvium is a type of alopecia.

Trichomoniasis is a parasitic protozoa infectious disease that also goes by the synonym trichomonas infection. It is a type of disease with a material basis in some Trichomonas. Trichomoniasis is defined as a disease caused by single-celled protozoan parasites Trichomonas vaginalis or Trichomonas tenax, which infect the urogenital tract and mouth, respectively.

Cholecystitis is a type of cholangitis and is characterized as a cholangitis that exhibits inflammation specifically located in the gallbladder. This condition is acknowledged to manifest some form of inflammation as part of its symptoms. Cholecystitis is also precisely known by several synonyms, including acute cholecystitis, chronic cholecystitis, acute and chronic cholecystitis, and acute on chronic cholecystitis.

Fallopian tube disease is the same as a disease that intersects with a condition having its location in the fallopian tube. It is a type of female reproductive system disease and also categorized under conditions that at least have the symptom of inflammation. Furthermore, fallopian tube disease is defined as a female reproductive system disease that is located in the fallopian tube.

Fallopian tube carcinoma is a type of fallopian tube cancer and a type of carcinoma that at least derives from some epithelial cell. It is defined as a fallopian tube cancer that is located in the fallopian tube. Furthermore, fallopian tube carcinoma has exact synonyms including cancer of the fallopian tube, carcinoma of fallopian tube, and fallopian tube Ca.

Fallopian tube cancer is identical to a type of cancer that intersects with a condition categorized as a disease located in the fallopian tube. It is a form of cancer concerning the female reproductive organs and is specifically a type of fallopian tube disease. The definition of fallopian tube cancer is a female reproductive organ cancer that is situated in the fallopian tube. Additionally, fallopian tube cancer is precisely referred to by several synonyms including fallopian tube neoplasm, malignant neoplasm of the uterine tube, malignant tumor of the fallopian tube, malignant tumour of the fallopian tube, neoplasm of the fallopian tube, tumor of the fallopian tube, and tumor, fallopian tube, malignant.

Fallopian tube leiomyosarcoma is defined as a fallopian tube cancer that derives from smooth muscle cells, and it is recognized as both a type of fallopian tube cancer and a type of leiomyosarcoma. This condition is synonymous with an entity that is at the intersection of leiomyosarcoma and a disease located in the fallopian tube.

Leiomyosarcoma is a type of smooth muscle cancer and has the definition of being a smooth muscle cancer that can arise almost anywhere in the body, but is most common in the uterus, abdomen, or pelvis. It is also exactly synonymous with Leiomyosarcomas.

Cerebral palsy is a type of brain disease that specifically affects the cerebrum and is caused by damage to the motor control centers of the developing brain during pregnancy, childbirth, or after birth. This disease impacts muscle movement and balance. Additionally, cerebral palsy is exactly synonymous with infantile cerebral palsy.

Fallopian tube carcinosarcoma is a type of fallopian tube cancer and is also defined as a fallopian tube cancer characterized by being a mixture of carcinoma and sarcoma, with a material basis in both epithelial tissue and connective tissue. This condition is located in the fallopian tube and is additionally referred to by exact synonyms, including fallopian tube malignant mixed Mullerian tumor and fallopian tube malignant mixed mesodermal (mullerian) tumor.

Fallopian tube adenosarcoma is a type of fallopian tube carcinosarcoma, which is defined as a fallopian tube carcinoma characterized by a mixture of carcinoma and sarcoma, having its material basis in both epithelial and connective tissues. It is also exactly synonymous with fallopian tube mullerian adenosarcoma.

Adenosarcoma is a type of carcinosarcoma and is defined as a carcinosarcoma that derives from simultaneously or consecutively in mesodermal tissue and glandular epithelium. It has an exact synonym, mullerian Adenosarcoma, and an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D018195.

Thymus lipoma is a type of benign neoplasm that is identified as both an endocrine organ and an immune system organ neoplasm. It is recognized as a specific form of lipoma and a disease of the thymus gland. Its origin is associated with adipocytes, indicating that it at least partially derives from fat cells. Furthermore, thymus lipoma is characterized by its location in the thymus, emphasizing its connection to diseases that have their location in the thymus. It is defined as an immune system organ benign neoplasm located in the thymus and deriving from fat cells, and it is also exactly synonymous with Thymolipoma.

:focal_chorioretinitis rdfs:subClassOf :chorioretinitis .
text: focal chorioretinitis is a type of chorioretinitis.

Rectal benign neoplasm is identical to an entity that is both a benign neoplasm and a disease located in the rectum. It is classified as a type of intestinal benign neoplasm and is defined as an intestinal benign neoplasm located in the rectum. Additionally, rectal benign neoplasm is exactly synonymous with "Rectal tumor," "neoplasm of rectum," and "rectum neoplasm."
Rectum lymphoma is a type of lymphoma, a type of rectum cancer, and a type of something that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. It has the exact synonym "Lymphoma of rectum."

Rectum malignant melanoma is a type of melanoma and also a type of rectum cancer. It is a disease that originates from melanocytes and is located in the rectum. Furthermore, rectum malignant melanoma is exactly synonymous with both malignant melanoma of the rectum and melanoma of the rectum.

Rectum cancer is identical to an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease with a location in the rectum. It is a type of colorectal cancer and has the definition of being a colorectal cancer located in the rectum. Rectum cancer is precisely synonymous with carcinoma of rectum, carcinoma of the rectum, malignant Rectal tumor, malignant neoplasm of rectum, malignant rectum tumor, malignant tumor of rectum, and rectal cancer. Additionally, rectum cancer has a related synonym which is cancer of rectum.

Rectum sarcoma is a type of sarcoma, and it is also a type of rectum cancer. Additionally, it is a type of entity that at least derives from some embryonic cell metazoa. Rectum sarcoma is defined as a sarcoma and malignant tumor of the rectum that is located in the rectum. It has the exact synonym "sarcoma of the rectum."

Rectum adenocarcinoma, also known exactly as Rectal adenocarcinoma, is a type of rectum cancer and a subtype of adenocarcinoma. This form of cancer is characterized by its origin from epithelial cells of glandular origin, making it a disease that falls at the intersection of conditions involving epithelial cells and those originating from glands. Furthermore, rectum adenocarcinoma is specifically located in the rectum, which is highlighted by its definition as a rectum cancer deriving from epithelial cells of glandular origin.
Lutembacher's syndrome is a type of atrial heart septal defect. It is exactly synonymous with both Lutembacher syndrome and Lutembacher's anomaly.
Chronic eustachian salpingitis is a type of otosalpingitis, which is defined as a persistent and long-lasting otosalpingitis. It has the exact synonym "chronic eustachian tube salpingitis."

:benign_giant_cell_tumor rdfs:subClassOf :bone_benign_neoplasm .
text: benign giant cell tumor is a type of bone benign neoplasm.

Otosalpingitis is a type of eustachian tube disease, defined as a eustachian tube disorder involving inflammation of the mucous membrane of the cartilagenous portion of the eustachian tube caused by acute nasopharyngitis, infection from some pathogenic microbes, or trauma of the tube. It is exactly synonymous with both Eustachian salpingitis and Eustachian tube salpingitis.
A neuroma is a type of benign neoplasm in the nervous system, which is defined as a nerve tissue tumor characterized by its noncancerous growth.

Preretinal fibrosis is a type of degeneration of the macula and posterior pole. It is also exactly synonymous with Macular puckering of the retina, Macular retinal puckering, and cellophane maculopathy.

Degeneration of the macula and posterior pole is a type of macular degeneration, which is exactly synonymous with degeneration of the macula and posterior pole of the retina, as well as degeneration of the macula or posterior pole.

Connective tissue cancer, also known by its exact synonyms tumor of connective tissue, connective tissue neoplasm, mesenchymal tissue malignant neoplasm, and neoplasm of connective tissues, is identified as the intersection of cancer and a disease that is located in some connective tissue. It is categorized both as a type of musculoskeletal system cancer and as a type of connective tissue disease. Moreover, it is defined as a musculoskeletal system cancer that is located in connective tissue.

Nezelof syndrome is a type of autosomal recessive disease and a type of T cell deficiency, which specifically stems from issues related to autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a T cell deficiency that results from the dysfunction or underdevelopment of the thymus. Furthermore, Nezelof syndrome is also known by several exact synonyms, including Nezelof's syndrome, T-cell immunodeficiency with thymic aplasia, TIDTA, thymic aplasia, and thymic dysplasia with normal immunoglobulins.

Hyperinsulinism is a type of pancreas disease and also falls under the category of glucose metabolism diseases. It is identified as a condition that affects at least some part of the pancreas as well as some endocrine gland. Additionally, hyperinsulinism is exactly synonymous with hyperinsulinemia.

Placenta cancer, also known as placental tumors, malignant placental tumor, malignant neoplasm of placenta, neoplasm of placenta, placental cancer, and primary malignant neoplasm of placenta, is defined as a female reproductive organ cancer located in the placenta. It is equivalent to the intersection of cancer and diseases that are at least located in the placenta. Furthermore, placenta cancer is categorized as a type of uterine cancer and a type of placenta disease.
Placental choriocarcinoma is a type of gestational choriocarcinoma that is characterized by its location in the placenta. It is also exactly synonymous with Choriocarcinoma of the Placenta.

Gestational choriocarcinoma is a type of choriocarcinoma that develops in the presence of a preceding gestational event. It is exactly synonymous with Gestational chorionepithelioma and Molar pregnancy with choriocarcinoma.

Exostosis is a type of hyperostosis and is defined as a hyperostosis that involves the formation of new bone on the surface of preexisting bone. It is exactly synonymous with several terms including bone spur, bony outgrowth, orbital exostosis, osteophyte, and swimmer's exostosis.

Anxiety disorder is a type of cognitive disorder defined as a cognitive disorder that involves an excessive, irrational dread of everyday situations. It has the exact synonyms "anxiety" and "anxiety state."
A communication disorder is a type of specific developmental disorder defined as a specific developmental disorder that involves developmental disorders of speech and language.

Encephalomalacia is a type of brain disease and also falls under the category of diseases that have a location in the cerebrum. It is defined as a brain disease characterized by cerebral softening located in the cerebrum, which has a material basis in injured or dead cells of the central nervous system.

Enthesopathy is a type of connective tissue disease characterized by damage of tissues located in the entheses, which are the sites of insertion of tendons or ligaments into bones or joint capsules. This condition presents with symptoms such as pain, swelling, and inflammation. Enthesopathy has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) database with the identifier D000070676.

Hepatitis B is a type of viral infectious disease that has a material basis in the Hepatitis B virus. It is transmitted through contact transmission, vehicle-borne fomite transmission, and vehicle-borne medical transmission, which includes sexual contact, blood transfusions, or fomites like needles or syringes. The disease manifests with several symptoms including joint pain, liver inflammation, loss of appetite, abdominal pain, nausea, jaundice, fever, vomiting, fatigue, acholic stool, and clay-colored bowel movements. Hepatitis B, also known as chronic hepatitis B or hepatitis B infection, is alternatively referred to as serum hepatitis. The definition of hepatitis B emphasizes that it results in inflammation located in the liver, caused by the Hepatitis B virus, and details its transmission methods as well as its symptoms.
Drug-induced hepatitis is a type of hepatitis and has the exact synonym "Drug-induced chronic hepatitis."

Hepatitis D, also known as Delta Hepatitis, is a type of viral infectious disease that specifically involves the liver. It is characterized by being a co-infection that requires both the Hepatitis B virus and the Hepatitis Delta virus for its occurrence. This disease manifests with a wide range of symptoms including confusion, drowsiness, lethargy, liver inflammation, nausea, anorexia, jaundice, sleep disturbances, coma, abnormal behavior, fatigue, acholic stools (clay-colored stools), and dark urine. The definition of Hepatitis D emphasizes that it results in inflammation in the liver, has a material basis in the Hepatitis Delta virus, which is an incomplete virus needing the helper function of the Hepatitis B virus for replication. This condition only occurs among individuals infected with the Hepatitis B virus and includes symptoms such as fatigue, lethargy, anorexia, nausea, jaundice, clay-colored stools, dark urine, changes in personality, sleep disturbances, confusion, abnormal behavior, somnolence, and coma.

Autoimmune hepatitis is a type of autoimmune disease of the gastrointestinal tract, which is characterized by inflammation located in the liver caused by the body's immune system attacking the liver cells. This condition is also known to have symptoms including some liver inflammation. Moreover, autoimmune hepatitis is precisely synonymous with Autoimmune chronic active hepatitis and autoimmune hepatitis with centrilobular necrosis.

Hyperostosis is a type of bone remodeling disease characterized by an abnormal growth located in the bone, which is defined as a bone remodeling disease resulting in abnormal growth. It is exactly synonymous with bone hypertrophy and hypertrophy of bone.
Acute maxillary sinusitis is a type of maxillary sinusitis characterized by a condition that lasts for less than 4 weeks. It is also precisely known as acute antritis.

Maxillary sinusitis is a type of sinusitis defined as a condition involving infection of the maxillary sinuses that results in pain or pressure over the cheeks just below the eyes, toothache, and headache.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:reactive_cutaneous_fibrous_lesion rdfs:subClassOf :skin_disease .
text: reactive cutaneous fibrous lesion is a type of skin disease.

Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is a type of anxiety disorder which is defined as an anxiety disorder resulting from a traumatic experience that leads to psychological trauma. Additionally, PTSD is exactly synonymous with traumatic neurosis.

Chronic mucocutaneous candidiasis is a type of candidiasis, a skin disease, and a nail disease. It is characterized by conditions that intersect at being a disease located in zones of skin and nails. Additionally, it is associated with a phenotype that includes scarring. The definition of chronic mucocutaneous candidiasis refers to a heterogeneous group of disorders characterized by recurrent or persistent superficial fungal infections. These infections are located in the skin, mucous membranes, or nails, resulting from T-cell defects. The causative agent is Candida species. Symptoms include scaling of skin lesions, thickening of nails, swollen periungal tissue, and scarring of the scalp.

Vulvar disease is identified as a condition that intersects with diseases located in the mammalian vulva, essentially making it a type of female reproductive system disease. It is defined as a female reproductive system disease that is located in the vulva.

Hereditary multiple exostoses is a type of autosomal dominant disease and an exostosis, which is classified as something that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. This condition is defined as an exostosis that has its material basis in a mutation on the genes EXT1, EXT2, and EXT3, resulting in multiple bony spurs throughout a child's growth. Furthermore, hereditary multiple exostoses is known by several exact synonyms, including Multiple congenital exostosis, Multiple exostosis syndromes, Osteochondromatosis syndrome, hereditary multiple exostoses 1, hereditary multiple exostoses 2, hereditary multiple exostoses 3, and multiple osteochondromas.

Vulvar nodular hidradenoma is a type of vulvar benign neoplasm, defined as a vulvar benign neoplasm that is characterized by nodules with cystic foci high in the dermis on gross examination and derives from the sweat gland distal excretory duct. It is histologically characterized by nests or lobules of cells resembling eccrine poroma with either clear cytoplasm or prominent squamous metaplasia, and lumina lined by cuboidal ductal cells or columnar secretory cells.
Nodular hidradenoma is a type of hidradenoma and has a related synonym: Eccrine nodular hidradenoma.

Vulvar syringoma is a type of vulvar benign neoplasm and something that at least has the symptom of some itching. It is defined as a vulvar benign neoplasm characterized by the comma tadpole-shaped tail of dilated, cystic eccrine ducts, derives from the eccrine sweat gland, and presents as multiple, small, soft, skin-colored-to-yellowish papules. Moreover, it has symptoms of vulvar discomfort and itching.

:syringoma rdfs:subClassOf :sweat_gland_benign_neoplasm .
text: syringoma is a type of sweat gland benign neoplasm.

Vulvar angiokeratoma is a type of vulvar benign neoplasm and is defined as a vulvar benign neoplasm characterized by numerous ectatic blood vessels present in the superficial dermis. It is also exactly synonymous with Fordyce angiokeratoma of the vulva.
Bartholin's gland benign neoplasm is a type of vestibular gland benign neoplasm and has exact synonyms including Bartholin gland neoplasm and tumor of Bartholin's gland.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:vulvar_squamous_papilloma rdfs:subClassOf :vulvar_squamous_tumor .
text: vulvar squamous papilloma is a type of vulvar squamous tumor.
A vulvar squamous tumor, which is a type of vulva cancer, is defined as a vulva cancer that has its material basis in squamous tissue.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:perinatal_intestinal_perforation rdfs:subClassOf :intestinal_perforation .
text: perinatal intestinal perforation is a type of intestinal perforation.
Intestinal perforation, which is a type of intestinal disease, is exactly synonymous with Perforation of the intestine.

Minor vestibular glands adenoma is a type of vestibular gland benign neoplasm, and it is also a type of adenoma. This condition intersects with entities that derive from epithelial cells and have their origin in glands. The definition of minor vestibular glands adenoma is a vestibular gland benign neoplasm located in the minor vestibular glands, composed of epithelial tissue where tumor cells form glands or gland-like structures. Additionally, adenoma of minor vestibular glands is a related synonym for minor vestibular glands adenoma.
Vulvar glandular tumor, a type of vulva cancer, is defined as a vulva cancer that has its material basis in glandular tissue.

Chondroid syringoma of the vulva is a type of vulvar benign neoplasm and a type of eccrine mixed tumor of the skin. Additionally, it is a type of condition that has its location in the mammalian vulva.

Eccrine mixed tumor of skin is a type of eccrine sweat gland neoplasm and has several exact synonyms. These include Eccrine mixed tumor, Eccrine mixed tumour, eccrine mixed tumour of skin, and mixed Eccrine neoplasm of the skin.

Vulvar trichoepithelioma is a type of vulvar benign neoplasm, defined as a vulvar benign neoplasm that derives from epithelial-mesenchymal origin cells. It is characterized by branching nests of basaloid cells, horn cysts, and abortive hair papillae, representing benign hamartomas of the pilosebaceous apparatus.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:transient_arthritis rdfs:subClassOf :arthropathy .
text: transient arthritis is a type of arthropathy.
Vulvar melanoma is a type of vulva cancer and it is defined as a vulva cancer that has its material basis in melanocytes. It is also exactly synonymous with malignant melanoma of the vulva.

Sweat gland cancer is defined as a condition that intersects the categories of cancer and diseases, particularly those located in the sweat gland. It is identified as a type of sweat gland disease as well as a type of skin cancer. Additionally, sweat gland cancer is exactly synonymous with both malignant neoplasm of the sweat gland and malignant tumor of the sweat gland.
Vulvar sarcoma is a type of vulva cancer, and it is defined as a vulva cancer that has its material basis in connective tissue. It is also exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the vulva.

Vulval Paget's disease is a type of vulva adenocarcinoma characterized by distinctive large cells with prominent cytoplasm, known as Paget cells. It is an intraepithelial neoplasm of epithelial origin that expresses apocrine or eccrine glandular-like features. This condition is also exactly synonymous with Paget's disease of vulva, Vulvar Paget's disease, and vulval Paget disease.

Vulva adenocarcinoma is a type of vulva carcinoma and also falls under the category of adenocarcinoma. It is defined as a vulva carcinoma that derives from epithelial cells of glandular origin, indicating that it is a type of cancer originating from epithelial cells that intersect with cells having a glandular origin. Moreover, vulva adenocarcinoma is exactly synonymous with adenocarcinoma of Vulva and is relatedly synonymous with adenocarcinoma of the vulva.
Heel spur is a type of exostosis and has a definition as an exostosis that results in an abnormal growth located in the calcaneus. Additionally, heel spur is related to the synonym calcaneal spur.

Vulva squamous cell carcinoma is a type of carcinoma that specifically affects the vulva and falls under the broader category of squamous cell carcinoma. It originates from squamous epithelial cells and is found in the mammalian vulva. This carcinoma is defined as a vulva carcinoma with a material basis in squamous cells, located in the epidermis of the vulvar tissue. It is precisely synonymous with Vulvar Epidermoid carcinoma and vulvar squamous cell carcinoma, and is also relatedly known as squamous cell carcinoma of the vulva.

Myotonia congenita is a type of physical disorder and muscle tissue disease that is characterized by slow muscle relaxation associated with hyperexcitation of the muscle fibers. It is also defined as a condition that at least has symptoms of muscle weakness and has its basis in some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. Furthermore, myotonia congenita has exact synonyms, including Batten Turner congenital myopathy and Thomsen and Becker disease.

Cystoisosporiasis is a type of coccidiosis that involves infection of the epithelial cells of the small intestine with Cystoisospora belli. This infection results in nonbloody diarrhea accompanied by crampy abdominal pain, malabsorption, and weight loss. Furthermore, cystoisosporiasis is characterized by symptoms that include at least abdominal cramps and diarrhea. Additionally, cystoisosporiasis is also known by its exact synonyms: Infection by Isospora belli and Isospora hominis, Isosporosis, and isosporiasis.

Coccidiosis is a type of parasitic protozoa infectious disease that occurs in the intestinal tract of animals and humans, caused by Coccidia protozoa. It is defined as a parasitic protozoa infectious disease, and individuals who are immunocompromised are at greater risk of developing the infection. Additionally, coccidiosis is also known by the related synonym intestinal coccidiosis.

B cell deficiency is a type of primary immunodeficiency disease, which is defined as a primary immunodeficiency disease caused by a lack of infection-fighting antibody-producing B cells (immunoglobulins) or B cells that are not functioning properly. It has exact synonyms such as B cell (antibody) deficiencies, Immunoglobulin heavy chain deficiency, and immunoglobulin heavy chain deletion.

Focal dermal hypoplasia, also known exactly as FDH, FODH, Goltz syndrome, and Goltz-Gorlin syndrome, is a type of syndrome and a specific form of X-linked dominant disease. It is characterized at birth by streaks of very thin skin (dermal hypoplasia), cutis aplasia, and telangiectases. The material basis of this syndrome involves at least some aspects of X-linked dominant inheritance, specifically a heterozygous mutation in the PORCN gene on chromosome Xp11.23.

Ectodermal dysplasia is a type of syndrome that is characterized by abnormal development in two or more ectodermal structures, including hair, nails, teeth, and sweat glands, without other systemic findings. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Congenital ectodermal defect and Congenital ectodermal dysplasia.

Pneumonic tularemia is a type of tularemia and a lung disease that is specifically located in the lungs. It is transmitted by airborne transmission and is characterized by symptoms such as pain, cough, and breathing problems. This condition is known by several exact synonyms including Pneumonic tularaemia, bronchopneumonic tularemia, and pulmonary tularemia. The detailed definition of pneumonic tularemia highlights that it involves breathing in dusts or aerosols containing the organisms, leading to symptoms like cough, chest pain, and difficulty breathing.

Tularemia is a primary bacterial infectious disease that has its material basis in Francisella tularensis. It can be transmitted in various ways including through deer fly bites (Chrysops sp), dog tick bites (Dermacentor variabilis), and contact with infected animal tissues. Additionally, the transmission of tularemia encompasses a range of methods such as contact transmission, vector-borne bite transmission, insect-borne transmission, and tick-borne transmission, illustrating the diverse ways this disease can spread.

Brain germinoma is a type of brain cancer, germ cell cancer, and something that at least derives from some germ cell. It is defined as a brain cancer characterized by abnormally proliferating cells that derive from germ cells. Additionally, brain germinoma has exact synonyms including germinoma of the brain and intracranial germinoma.

Atypical teratoid rhabdoid tumor is a type of brain cancer characterized by its usual location in the brain, though it can occur anywhere in the central nervous system. It has several exact synonyms, including Atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor, Atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumour, Rhabdoid tumor of the CNS, Rhabdoid tumour of the CNS, and atypical teratoid rhabdoid tumour. Furthermore, it is relatedly referred to as AT/RT and rhabdoid tumor predisposition syndrome.

Brain sarcoma is a type of brain cancer and is exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the brain. It is defined as a brain cancer characterized by abnormally proliferating cells, which originates from the embryonic mesoderm.

Central nervous system sarcoma is a type of sarcoma and also a type of central nervous system cancer. It falls under the category of cancers that intersect with conditions deriving at least partly from embryonic cell metazoa. It is defined as a central nervous system cancer that develops from transformed cells of mesenchymal origin located in the brain and spine, with a material basis in abnormally proliferating cells that derive from the mesoderm. Additionally, central nervous system sarcoma has an exact synonym: sarcoma of the CNS.

Temporal lobe neoplasm, which is the same as something that intersects cancer and a disease with a location in the temporal lobe, is a type of cerebrum cancer. Moreover, it has exact synonyms including malignant neoplasm of temporal lobe, neoplasm of temporal lobe, and tumor of Temporal Lobe.

Paraurethral gland neoplasm is a type of urethral benign neoplasm, which is a category of disease localized in the paraurethral gland. It is exactly synonymous with both neoplasm of paraurethral glands and tumor of the Paraurethral gland.
