@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:teeth_hard_tissue_disease rdfs:subClassOf :tooth_disease .
text: teeth hard tissue disease is a type of tooth disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:urethral_urothelial_papilloma rdfs:subClassOf :urethral_benign_neoplasm .
text: urethral urothelial papilloma is a type of urethral benign neoplasm.

Urethra leiomyoma is a type of leiomyoma, and it is also categorized as a type of urethral benign neoplasm, as well as a condition that at least derives from some smooth muscle cell. It is defined as an urethral benign neoplasm that derives from smooth muscle cells. Moreover, urethra leiomyoma has an exact synonym, which is leiomyoma of the urethra.
Ovarian malignant mesothelioma, a type of ovarian cancer, is defined as an ovarian cancer that derives from mesothelial tissue.
A malignant ovarian cyst, which is a type of ovarian cancer, is defined as an ovarian cancer characterized by a cystic structure.

Ovary sarcoma is a type of sarcoma and also a type of ovarian cancer, which originates from some embryonic cell metazoa. It is defined as an ovarian cancer with a material basis in abnormally proliferating cells that derive from the embryonic mesoderm. Additionally, ovary sarcoma is exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the ovary.

Tuberculous oophoritis is a type of ovarian disease and a type of urogenital tuberculosis, which is characterized as a disease that at least has a location in the ovary. It is defined as an urogenital tuberculosis that results in inflammation located in the ovary.

Urogenital tuberculosis is a type of extrapulmonary tuberculosis that is defined as an extrapulmonary tuberculosis located in the urogenital system. It is also related to and synonymously known as Genitourinary tuberculosis.

Ovarian lymphoma is a type of lymphoma, a type of ovarian cancer, and a type of something that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. It is defined as an ovarian cancer that arises from lymphocytes.

Malignant ovarian surface epithelial stromal neoplasm is a type of ovary epithelial cancer defined as an ovary epithelial cancer that arises from the surface epithelium of the ovary and has a material basis in epithelial and stromal tissue.

Ovary epithelial cancer is a type of ovarian cancer and carcinoma that at least derives from some epithelial cell. It is defined as an ovarian cancer that derives from the ovarian surface epithelium. Furthermore, ovary epithelial cancer has an exact synonym: Ovarian Surface Epithelial-Stromal tumor.

Ovarian Wilms cancer is a type of ovarian cancer and is defined as a malignant neoplasm of the ovary and nephroblastoma that is located in the ovaries. It is also related to the synonym ovarian Wilms' tumor.

Nephroblastoma is a type of kidney cancer and is defined as a kidney cancer that affects the kidneys and is typically located in children. It has the exact synonym "adult nephroblastoma" and is also relatedly known as Wilms' tumor.
Malignant ovarian germ cell neoplasm is a type of ovarian germ cell cancer, which also has exact synonyms including malignant ovarian germ cell tumor and malignant germ cell tumor of the ovary.

Ovarian germ cell cancer is a type of ovarian cancer, defined as an ovarian cancer that originates in the germ (egg) cells of the ovary. It is precisely referred to by synonyms such as germ cell neoplasm of ovary and germ cell tumor of ovary. Additionally, ovarian germ cell cancer is also relatedly known as ovarian germ cell tumor.

Dental caries is a type of teeth hard tissue disease characterized by damage to a tooth that can happen when decay-causing bacteria in your mouth make acids that attack the tooth’s surface, or enamel. It has exact synonyms which include Dental caries extending into pulp, Dental caries of smooth surface, and Dental caries pit and fissure.

Nasal cavity disease is the same as an intersection of conditions that are diseases and have a location in the nasal cavity, indicating that at least one disease exists with its location being the nasal cavity. Furthermore, nasal cavity disease is categorized as a type of nose disease.
Enamel caries is a type of dental caries and it has several exact synonyms. These synonyms include Dental caries limited to enamel, primary dental caries, and simple dental cavity.

Vaginitis is a type of vaginal disease and a type of condition that, at the very least, manifests some inflammation as a symptom. It is defined as a vaginal disease characterized by inflammation of the vagina.

Eyelid benign neoplasm is defined as the intersection of a benign neoplasm and a disease that is located at least on the eyelid. This condition is a type of skin benign neoplasm as well as a type of eyelid disease. Additionally, eyelid benign neoplasm is exactly synonymous with the term "tumor of the eyelid."

Ocular cancer is defined as a condition that intersects with being a type of cancer and a disease that is located in the eye. It is categorized as a type of sensory system cancer as well as a type of eye disease. Ocular cancer is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation within the eye. Furthermore, ocular cancer is precisely synonymous with several terms including ocular tumor, eye neoplasm, malignant eye neoplasm, neoplasm of eye, and neoplasm of eye proper.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:carbuncle rdfs:subClassOf :pyoderma ;
    :has_exact_synonym "Carbuncle and furuncle of buttock"@en,
        "Carbuncle and furuncle of face"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of any part of face except eye"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of foot"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of gluteal region"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of hand"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of leg except foot"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of neck"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of trunk"@en,
        "carbuncle and furuncle of upper arm and forearm"@en .
text: Carbuncle is a type of pyoderma and has various exact synonyms based on its location. These synonyms include Carbuncle and furuncle of the buttock, face, any part of the face except the eye, foot, gluteal region, hand, leg except foot, neck, trunk, and upper arm and forearm.

Ascending colon cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease located in the ascending colon. It is a type of colon cancer and has several exact synonyms, including Ca ascending colon, malignant neoplasm of right colon, and malignant tumor of ascending colon.
Post-surgical hypoinsulinemia, which is a type of endocrine pancreas disease, is exactly synonymous with Postsurgical hypoinsulinemia.
Amelogenesis imperfecta is a type of dental enamel hypoplasia characterized by abnormal enamel formation.

Colon cancer is the same as something that is an intersection of cancer and something that is at least a disease located in the colon. It is a type of colonic disease as well as a type of colorectal cancer. Furthermore, colon cancer is defined as a colorectal cancer that is located in the colon.
Acute perichondritis of the pinna is a type of perichondritis of the auricle, defined by a perichondritis of the auricle that has a sudden onset and a short course.

Factor XIII deficiency is a type of autosomal recessive and blood coagulation disease that specifically has its material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is characterized by various symptoms including bleeding, epistaxis (nosebleeds), gum bleeding, menorrhagia (heavy menstrual bleeding), abnormal scar formation, abnormal wound healing, and features such as hemarthrosis (bleeding into joint spaces). The disease has a detailed definition: it is a blood coagulation disorder marked by easy bleeding, which includes symptoms like prolonged umbilical cord bleeding, epistaxis, gum bleeding, menorrhagia, recurrent miscarriages, abnormal scar formation and wound healing, and hemarthrosis. This condition is the result of autosomal recessive inheritance of mutations in the F13A1 or F13B gene, which encodes Factor XIII, also known as fibrin stabilizing factor. Factor XIII deficiency is also known by several exact synonyms: Factor XIII deficiency disease, Hereditary factor XIII deficiency disease, and deficiency, Laki-Lorand factor.
Hemorrhagic disease is a type of blood coagulation disease and it has an exact synonym, Hemorrhagic diathesis.

Factor VII deficiency is a type of autosomal recessive and blood coagulation disease, which has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is characterized by symptoms such as bleeding, epistaxis, gum bleeding, and menorrhagia, as well as features like hemarthrosis. Specifically, it is defined as a blood coagulation disorder characterized by easy bleeding, including symptoms like epistaxis, bleeding of the gums, menorrhagia, and occasionally hemarthrosis, all due to autosomal recessive inheritance of mutations in the F7 gene, which encodes for coagulation factor VII, a crucial element in the clotting cascade. Additionally, Factor VII deficiency is synonymously known as deficiency, stable and has exact matches in OMIM with the code 227500 and in ORDO with the code 327.

Factor V deficiency is a type of disease that is autosomal recessive, related to blood coagulation, and has a material basis in some form of autosomal recessive inheritance. It is exactly synonymous with Hereditary hypoproaccelerinaemia, Labile factor deficiency, Proaccelerin deficiency, and deficiency, labile.

Bernard Soulier Syndrome is a type of autosomal recessive disease and a blood coagulation disease that has material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance and at least has symptoms such as bleeding. It is characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of mucosal bleeding, purpuric skin bleeding, epistaxis, and menorrhagia with prolonged bleeding times, enlarged platelets, and absence of platelet aggregation in response to von Willebrand factor. This is due to mutations in the GP1BA, GP1BB, or GP9 genes, which are subunits of the platelet membrane von Willebrand factor receptor complex, glycoprotein Ib. Bernard Soulier Syndrome is also known by several exact synonyms, including Bernard-Soulier thrombopathy, Giant platelet syndrome, Hemorrhagic dystrophic thrombocytopenia, and Thrombopathy, Bernard-Soulier.

Blood platelet disease is the same as something that intersects with something that is a disease and something that, at the very least, has a location in some platelets. Furthermore, blood platelet disease is a type of blood coagulation disease. It is defined as a blood coagulation disease characterized by an abnormal increase or decrease in platelets or platelet dysfunction. Additionally, blood platelet disease has exact synonyms, including Thrombocytopathy and platelet disorder.

Glanzmann's thrombasthenia is a type of blood platelet disease, which is also known as a type of disorder that affects at least one location in the platelet. It is defined as a blood coagulation disease characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of failure of platelet aggregation and absent or diminished clot retraction. This condition has a material basis in mutation in the ITGA2B or ITGB3 genes on chromosome 17q21.32. Glanzmann's thrombasthenia is exactly synonymous with several terms including BDPLT2, Glanzmann thrombasthenia, Glycoprotein IIb/IIIa defect, Thrombocytasthenia, deficiency of GP IIb-IIIa complex, deficiency of glycoprotein complex IIb-IIIa, deficiency of platelet fibrinogen receptor, platelet glycoprotein IIb-IIIa deficiency, platelet-type bleeding disorder 2, and thrombasthenia of Glanzmann and Naegeli.

Perichondritis of the auricle is the same as something that intersects otitis externa and a condition that has a location in the pinna, indicating it is a specific type of otitis externa. Furthermore, it is characterized by symptoms such as pain and fever, as it belongs to a category of conditions that manifest these symptoms. The definition of perichondritis of the auricle is an otitis externa that involves the infection of the tissue surrounding the cartilage of the earlobe (pinna), ear canal, or both, often resulting from injury, burns, insect bites, ear piercing, or a boil on the ear. The common bacterial causative agent associated with this condition is Pseudomonas aeruginosa, with symptoms including redness, pain, fever, swelling of the earlobe, and pus accumulation between the cartilage and the surrounding layer of connective tissue. Additionally, perichondritis of the auricle is exactly synonymous with "Perichondritis and chondritis of pinna" as well as "Perichondritis of pinna," highlighting the condition's specific focus and manifestation within medical terminology.

Factor X deficiency is a type of autosomal recessive disease and a type of blood coagulation disease, which also falls under something that at least has a material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a blood coagulation disease characterized by the partial or complete absence of factor X activity in the blood. Additionally, Factor X deficiency has the exact synonym "disease, Stuart-Prower" and has exact matches with OMIM:227600 and ORDO:328.
Platelet storage pool deficiency is a type of blood platelet disease that is also exactly synonymous with Dense body defect, Platelet dense granule deficiency, and Platelet storage pool defect.

Essential thrombocythemia is a type of myeloproliferative neoplasm and also falls under the category of conditions that at least have the symptom of some hemorrhage. It is defined as a myeloproliferative neoplasm characterized by sustained thrombocytosis in the blood, increased numbers of large, mature megakaryocytes in the bone marrow, and episodes of thrombosis and/or hemorrhage, resulting in the overproduction of platelets. Additionally, essential thrombocythemia is known by several exact synonyms, including Essential thrombocythaemia, familial thrombocytosis, hemorrhagic thrombocythemia, hereditary thrombocythemia, and primary Thrombocytosis.

Myeloproliferative neoplasm is a type of myeloid neoplasm and is defined as a myeloid neoplasm characterized by a group of slow-growing blood cancers in which large numbers of abnormal red blood cells, white blood cells, or platelets grow and spread in the bone marrow and the peripheral blood. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms including CMPD, CMPD, U, and chronic myeloproliferative disease.
Thrombocytosis is a type of blood platelet disease and is characterized by the presence of high platelet counts in the blood. It is also known by its exact synonym, Thrombocythaemia.

Factor XI deficiency is a type of autosomal genetic disease and a type of blood coagulation disease, which at least has a material basis in some autosomal inheritance and has symptoms that include some bleeding. It is characterized by a deficiency of the factor XI clotting factor and mild prolonged bleeding, especially of mucosal sites following trauma. This condition has its material basis in homozygous, compound heterozygous, or heterozygous mutation of the coagulation factor XI gene on chromosome 4q35.2. Factor XI deficiency is also known by several exact synonyms including Congenital factor XI deficiency, Hereditary factor XI deficiency disease, Rosenthal's disease, hemophilia C, and plasma thromboplastin antecedent deficiency.

Basilar artery insufficiency is equivalent to a condition that falls at the intersection of a syndrome and a disease located specifically in the basilar artery. It is classified as a type of artery disease, transient cerebral ischemia, and a syndrome. Furthermore, basilar artery insufficiency is precisely synonymous with Basilar artery syndrome.

Factor XII deficiency is a type of disease that falls under several categories: it is an autosomal recessive disease, a blood coagulation disease, and something that inherently has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. This condition is defined as a blood coagulation disease characterized by a prolonged PTT time without clinical symptoms, which arises from a mutation in the F12 gene located on chromosome 5q33. Moreover, it is precisely synonymous with Factor XII deficiency disease, Hageman Factor deficiency, and deficiency, Hageman.

Focal epilepsy is a type of epilepsy characterized by seizures that are preceded by an isolated disturbance of a cerebral function and arise from an epileptic focus, a small portion of the brain that serves as the irritant driving the epileptic response. It is also exactly synonymous with localisation-related epilepsy and partial epilepsy.

Prothrombin deficiency is a type of autosomal recessive disease and thrombophilia, which is characterized by bleeding symptoms due to low levels of circulating prothrombin. It has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance of homozygous or compound heterozygous mutations in the gene encoding coagulation factor II, also known as prothrombin, on chromosome 11p11. This condition is also known by several synonyms: Congenital factor II deficiency, Hereditary factor II deficiency disease, hypoprothrombinemia, and is relatedly referred to as Factor II deficiency.

Congenital afibrinogenemia is a type of autosomal recessive disease, physical disorder, and blood coagulation disease that at least has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance and has its basis in some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. It is defined as a blood coagulation disease characterized by impaired blood clotting resulting from a deficiency of the fibrinogen protein, also known as coagulation factor I. Moreover, congenital afibrinogenemia is exactly synonymous with Factor I deficiency and Fibrinogen deficiency.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hepatitis rdfs:subClassOf :liver_disease ;
    :has_exact_synonym "acute and subacute liver necrosis"@en,
        "acute hepatitis"@en,
        "acute/subac. necrosis of liver"@en,
        "animal hepatitis"@en,
        "chronic hepatitis"@en,
        "chronic persistent hepatitis"@en .
text: Hepatitis is a type of liver disease which has several exact synonyms including acute and subacute liver necrosis, acute hepatitis, acute/subacute necrosis of liver, animal hepatitis, chronic hepatitis, and chronic persistent hepatitis.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:granulomatous_hepatitis rdfs:subClassOf :hepatitis .
text: granulomatous hepatitis is a type of hepatitis.

Transient cerebral ischemia is a type of brain ischemia characterized by ischemia of brief duration and without resultant tissue death. It is also known by its exact synonyms: TIA, TIA - Transient ischaemic attack, Transient cerebral ischaemia, Transient ischemic attacks, and transient ischemic attack.

Spondylosis is a type of spinal disease and also a type of bone structure disease, specifically involving the vertebral column. It is defined as a bone structure disease that involves degeneration between vertebrae located in the vertebral column. Spondylosis has several exact synonyms, including Lumbar spondylosis with myelopathy, Spondylogenic compression of lumbar spinal cord, Spondylogenic compression of thoracic spinal cord, Thoracic or lumbar spondylosis with myelopathy, Lumbosacral spondylosis without myelopathy, and Spondylosis with myelopathy.

A syndrome is defined as a disease characterized by a group of signs and symptoms that occur together and characterize a particular abnormality. It is identified as the same as something that is at the intersection of a disease and something that, at the very least, has a disease based on some symptom. Furthermore, a syndrome is classified as a type of disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypertrophic_elongation_of_cervix rdfs:subClassOf :cervix_disease .
text: hypertrophic elongation of cervix is a type of cervix disease.

Cervix disease is the same as something that is both a disease and is located in the uterine cervix, representing an intersection of these characteristics. Additionally, cervix disease is a type of uterine disease and is defined as an uterine disease that is located in the cervix.

Osteochondrodysplasia is identical to a condition that intersects both a disease and something characterized by at least one phenotype of skeletal dysplasia. Furthermore, osteochondrodysplasia is classified as a type of bone development disease and is defined as a bone development disease that results in defective development of cartilage or bone. Additionally, osteochondrodysplasia is precisely synonymous with several terms including Cartilage Development Disorder, Congenital Anomaly of Cartilage, Osteochondrodysplasia Syndrome, Chondrodystrophy, and Skeletal Dysplasia.

Ankylosis is a type of arthropathy and is defined as an arthropathy where there is a stiffness of a joint, resulting from injury or disease. The rigidity may be complete or partial and may be due to inflammation of the tendinous or muscular structures outside the joint or of the tissues of the joint itself. Furthermore, ankylosis has an exact match with MESH:D000844.

Vulvovaginal candidiasis is a type of vaginal disease, which is also a type of candidiasis. This condition is characterized by symptoms such as dyspareunia, paresthesia, and rash, and notably, the disease primarily affects the vagina. It is defined as a candidiasis involving fungal infection of the vaginal mucous membranes in women caused by Candida albicans, with symptoms including intense vulval pruritus, burning, erythema, and dyspareunia associated with a creamy white, curd-like discharge. Furthermore, vulvovaginal candidiasis is also known by exact synonyms such as Candidal cervix, Candidal vulvovaginitis, Candidiasis of vulva and vagina, and Monilial vulvovaginitis.

Vulvovaginitis is a type of disease affecting the female reproductive system, characterized by inflammation of the vagina and vulva. It is also recognized by the exact synonym Vulvo-vaginitis. This condition is associated with inflammation, marking it as a disease that involves at least some symptom of inflammation.

Pharyngitis is a type of upper respiratory tract disease that involves inflammation of the throat or pharynx resulting from bacterial, viral, fungal infections, or irritants like pollutants, chemical substances, and smoking, often referred to as a sore throat. The symptoms of pharyngitis include pain during swallowing, enlarged tonsils coated with a white discharge, runny nose, cough, and slight fever. Additionally, pharyngitis is characterized by having at least some symptoms such as rhinorrhea, cough, and low-grade fever. It is also known by various synonyms, including Inflamed throat, Persistent sore throat, Pharyngeal disorder, Pharyngitis - acute, Sore throat - chronic, acute pharyngitis, acute sore throat, chronic pharyn/nasopharyngitis, chronic pharyngitis, chronic pharyngitis and nasopharyngitis, and chronic sore throat. Moreover, pharyngitis has a related synonym, pharyngeal disease.

Gonadal disease is the same as something that is an intersection of a disease and something that, at the very least, has its location in the gonads. It is a type of endocrine system disease. Furthermore, gonadal disease is defined as an endocrine system disease that is located in the gonads.

Hidradenitis suppurativa is a type of hidradenitis and is characterized by chronic inflammation of the apocrine sweat glands. This condition is also known as Acne inversa, familial. It includes symptoms such as inflammation, pain, abscesses, and specifically chronic inflammation. More detailed symptoms include painful nodules, abscesses, sinus tract formation, scarring, erythema, pruritis, and pain. The underlying cause is chronic inflammation of the apocrine sweat glands which leads to recurrent folliculitis and an immune response that exacerbates the inflammation.

Hidradenitis is a type of sweat gland disease, also known precisely as Hydradenitis. It is characterized by inflammation of the apocrine sweat glands and exhibits symptoms such as erythema, edema, papules, plaques, pruritus, and pain. Additionally, this condition involves symptoms including at least some inflammation, pain, papules, and edema.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:keratopathy rdfs:subClassOf :corneal_disease .
text: keratopathy is a type of corneal disease.

Capillary lymphangioma is the same as something that intersects lymphangioma and something that is at least a disease located in some capillary. It is a type of capillary disease as well as a type of lymphangioma. Additionally, capillary lymphangioma is related to cutaneous lymphangioma as a synonym.

A female reproductive system disease is identified as a condition that is both a disease and specifically affects the female reproductive system, which includes the uterus, vagina, cervix, ovaries, or fallopian tubes. This type of disease is a subset of reproductive system diseases. Furthermore, it is defined as a reproductive system disease that impairs the ability to reproduce due to its location in the female reproductive system.

Leptospirosis is a primary bacterial infectious disease that is based on the bacteria Leptospira. It is transmitted through contact with water, food, or soil contaminated with urine from infected animals, which involves a combination of contact transmission and vehicle-borne ingestion transmission. The disease manifests with several symptoms, including jaundice, chills, fever, muscle pain, hepatomegaly (enlarged liver), left upper quadrant abdominal rigidity, and possibly more.

Moreover, leptospirosis is also known by several exact synonyms: Fort Bragg fever, Leptospirosis icterohaemorrhagica, Rat Catcher's Yellows, Weil's disease, nanukayami fever, and spirochetal jaundice.

Lateral sclerosis is a type of motor neuron disease which is characterized by painless but progressive weakness and stiffness of the muscles of the legs. This disease exhibits symptoms such as muscle weakness and progressive weakness. Additionally, lateral sclerosis is also known by its exact synonyms, adult-onset primary lateral sclerosis and primary lateral sclerosis.

Spondylolysis is a type of disease that pertains to both the spinal and bone structure. It specifically involves a defect in the lumbar vertebral column, indicating that it is located in some part of the vertebral column. The definition of spondylolysis is a bone structure disease that involves a defect located in the lumbar vertebral column.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

text: atrophy of prostate is a type of prostate disease.

Stereotypic movement disorder is a type of specific developmental disorder, which is characterized by repeated, rhythmic, purposeless movements or activities such as head banging, nail biting, or body rocking. Moreover, it has exact synonyms which include Stereotyped repetitive movements and Stereotypy habit disorder.

Motor neuron disease is the same as a condition that is both a disease and has a location specifically in motor neurons. It is classified as a type of neurodegenerative disease. Moreover, motor neuron disease is defined as a neurodegenerative disease that is located in the motor neurons.

Nocardiosis is an opportunistic bacterial infectious disease and is exactly synonymous with Nocardia infectious disease. It is defined as an infectious disease that results in disseminated infection in immunocompromised hosts and is caused by Nocardia asteroides. The infection manifests symptoms such as pneumonia, cellulitis, lesions in the brain or meninges, and ascending regional lymphadenopathy. Moreover, nocardiosis is characterized by features including pneumonia and symptoms like cellulitis and lymphadenopathy.

Malt worker's lung is a type of extrinsic allergic alveolitis, defined as an extrinsic allergic alveolitis caused by inhalation of fungal spores of Aspergillus clavatus and Aspergillus fumigatus from moldy barley. It is also exactly synonymous with Malt workers' lung, Malt-workers' lung, alveolitis due to Aspergillus clavatus, and malt worker lung.

Brain ischemia is a type of ischemia, cerebrovascular disease, and something that at least disease has location some brain. It is defined as an ischemia that is characterized by insufficient blood flow to the brain to meet metabolic demand. Furthermore, brain ischemia has exact synonyms including Ischaemic encephalopathy, Ischemic encephalopathy, and cerebral ischemia.
Obstructive lung disease is a type of lung disease that is characterized by the narrowing of pulmonary airways. It is also exactly synonymous with respiratory airway obstruction.

Gastroenteritis is a type of gastrointestinal system disease characterized by a range of symptoms including abdominal cramp, abdominal discomfort, loss of appetite, nausea, diarrhea, cramps, and vomiting. It is defined as a gastrointestinal system infectious disease that involves inflammation of the lining of the stomach and small and large intestines. This condition can be caused by viruses, bacteria, or parasites, as well as chemicals and drugs. The key symptoms associated with gastroenteritis are diarrhea, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, cramps, and discomfort in the abdomen. Additionally, gastroenteritis is synonymously known as cholera morbus and infectious colitis, enteritis, and gastroenteritis. It has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) database with the identifier D005759.

Viral gastritis is a type of gastritis and a type of viral infectious disease that has a material basis in some viruses. It is characterized by symptoms such as bloating, dyspepsia, abdominal pain, nausea, and vomiting. Additionally, viral gastritis can feature gastric ulcers. It is defined as a gastrointestinal system infectious disease that involves inflammation of the stomach lining caused by viruses, leading to symptoms including abdominal pain, indigestion, ulcer formation, abdominal bloating, nausea, and vomiting.

Mandibular cancer is defined as a type of jaw cancer that affects your lower jawbone. It is the same as an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is, at the very least, a disease located in the mandible. This condition is precisely referred to as malignant neoplasm of inferior maxilla, malignant neoplasm of the lower jaw bone, mandible cancer, and neoplasm of mandible. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of mandible and mandibular neoplasm.

Crouzon syndrome is a type of craniosynostosis and has a definition as a craniosynostosis that involves premature fusion of certain skull bones. This early fusion prevents the skull from growing normally and affects the shape of the head and face. Furthermore, the disease is associated with mutations in the FGFR2 gene. It also has an exact synonym, Craniofacial Dysostosis, and a related synonym, Crouzon's disease.

Colon adenocarcinoma is a type of colon carcinoma and a type of adenocarcinoma. It is also a type of something that at least derives from something with an intersection of something that is an epithelial cell and something that at least has origin in some gland. Moreover, colon adenocarcinoma has a definition as a colon carcinoma that derives from epithelial cells of glandular origin. Additionally, it has exact synonyms including Colonic adenocarcinoma and adenocarcinoma of the colon, along with a related synonym, adenocarcinoma of the colon.
Craniosynostosis is a type of synostosis and is defined as a synostosis that results in premature fusion located in the skull. It also has the exact synonym "Premature closure of cranial sutures."
Polyclonal hypergammaglobulinemia is a type of plasma protein metabolism disease and is a condition that at least has the symptom of some hypergammaglobulinemia.
Plasma protein metabolism disease is a type of inherited metabolic disorder characterized by a malfunction in plasma protein metabolism.
Monoclonal paraproteinemia is a type of plasma protein metabolism disease and it has an exact synonym, Monoclonal paraproteinaemia.
Generalized atherosclerosis, a type of atherosclerosis, also has an exact synonym: Generalised atherosclerosis.
Arteriosclerotic cardiovascular disease is a type of arteriosclerosis and has the exact synonym Cardiovascular arteriosclerosis.
Arteriosclerosis is a type of artery disease characterized by a thickening and hardening of arterial walls in the arteries, and it is also known as Arteriosclerotic vascular disease.

A colonic benign neoplasm is the same as something that intersects lymphangioma and something that, as a disease, is located in the colon. It is categorized as a type of lymphangioma, intestinal benign neoplasm, and colonic disease. Additionally, it is a type of condition where the disease is situated in the colon. The definition of a colonic benign neoplasm is an intestinal benign neoplasm that is located in the colon. It is also known by several exact synonyms including Colonic Mass, Colonic tumor, colon neoplasm, and neoplasm of colon.
Iron metabolism disease, which is a type of mineral metabolism disease, has the exact synonyms "disorder of iron metabolism" and "iron disorder."

Hemochromatosis is a type of metal metabolism disorder characterized by the accumulation of iron in various organs of the body. It is also exactly synonymous with haemochromatosis, diabetes bronze, and iron storage disorder.

Myelophthisic anemia is a type of aplastic anemia, which falls under the category of conditions that exhibit some form of anemia as a symptom. It is defined as an aplastic anemia characterized by the displacement of hemopoietic bone-marrow tissue either by fibrosis, tumors, or granulomas. Myelophthisic anemia is also known by its exact synonyms: ANEMIA LEUKOERYTHROBLASTIC, Anemia, leukoerythroblastic, and Leukoerythroblastosis. Additionally, it has a related synonym, myelophthisis.

Anemia is a type of hematopoietic system disease and is defined as a hematopoietic system disease that is characterized by a decrease in the normal number of red blood cells. It has the exact synonym "anaemia" and an exact match with MESH:D000740.
Macrocytic anemia is a type of anemia and has exact synonyms such as ANEMIA MACROCYTIC and Macrocytic anaemia.
